quests.name: Unpious Peons
quests.description: Those in-fur-nal Jagras keep messing with my visits to the Shrine Ruins. They're after the offur-ings I bring with me, those rude, blasphemous fiends! Send them running with their tails between their legs!

quests.name: Fungal Frustrations
quests.description: I've been dreaming of opening my own restaurant, but I spent so much time experimenting with the menu that I ran out of ingredients! I'll never be able to open if I don't get some more. Think you can help me out?

quests.name: Help With Maintenance
quests.description: I'm fixin' up the ol' camp, but I'm out of raw materials. Can't go get more 'cause everywhere ya go, Izuchi are snappin' and slashin' at ya. Think you can get 'em to scram so I can go get what I need?

quests.name: Roly-poly Lanterns
quests.description: Firelanterns are, like, so pretty! So red. So round. Something about them is simply magical. I totally want see them all the time so maybe I should put 'em in my room? What do you say? Think you can get me some?

quests.name: Grizzly Glutton
quests.description: This is terrible... If it goes on eating this much, there won't be a single fish left for us to catch! Hunt that thing before all the fish totally vanish from our rivers, will ya?

quests.name: Plump and Juicy
quests.description: Raftshells are just SO good. That gooeyness is to die for! And I almost did 'cause I couldn't stop stuffin' my face with 'em... Now my wife says I'm not allowed to have 'em anymore, but I can't take it!—I HAVE to have 'em! Think you can sneak me a few?

quests.name: A Frosty Paradise
quests.description: The darndest thing keeps happening. Every time I use this path, I fall asleep! When I wake up, my stuff is all chewed up! I know this place is infested with monsters...maybe they're behind this! You gotta do something or my biz is done for!

quests.name: Out Cold
quests.description: A Great Baggi and its little fur-iends were being a nuisance in the Fur-ost Islands, so I went to teach 'em a lesson. But when I got there, I passed out. Was it the cold? Just thinking about it makes me...so...slee—ZZZzzz...

quests.name: Rabid Rabbit
quests.description: I went hunting for some food but came across a Lagombi. I am NOT trying to get eaten by that thing. Hunter do you think you can take care of it for me, please?

quests.name: Great Izuchi, Great Pain
quests.description: A stupid Great Izuchi's going crazy at the Shrine Ruins, meaning my ingredients supplier is seriously in danger! Can you deal with that dumb Great Izuchi so my supplier can deliver the ingredients?

quests.name: Case of the Creepy Crawlies
quests.description: Some kids were telling us about all the bugs at the Shrine Ruins. Creepy crawly bugs...bugs that fly—yuck! I am NOT going there with all those bugs! Can you go out and exterminate those pests!?
quests.objective: Slay a total of 14 Altaroth or Bnahabra

quests.name: Hmm, Not So Tasty...
quests.description: Meow I'll never learn to cook meat! Too fast and it's raw, too slow and it's burnt... I need more purr-actice but I'm all out of Popo Tongues. Think you can get me some more?

quests.name: Can't Stomach the Thought
quests.description: During a survey of the Frost Islands, I was attacked by a Tetranadon and found myself inside its gut! I managed to escape, but others might not be so lucky. Please hunt it before someone gets eaten!

quests.name: Walking on Eggshells
quests.description: Blasted Kulu-Ya-Ku always stealing my Wyvern Eggs! I've tried and tried to make my way through the Sandy Plains but they get the jump on me every single time!

quests.name: Fightin' Dirty
quests.description: Ptoeey! Look at me! Covered from head to toe in mud! All because a stupid Barroth attacked me! Now all the mushrooms I gathered are ruined! Just great! Can you go and bash that Barroth, please!?

quests.name: Obnoxious Lord, Noxious Monster
quests.description: Oh dear... The lord's son heard a Great Wroggi was in the Flooded Forest and went out to hunt it. What a fool. Surely he'll run at the first sign of danger. Can you hunt the creature before my lord gets hurt.

quests.name: Spongy Oasis
quests.description: You know how Royal Ludroth hide is all spongey and absorbs lots of water, right? If we get a bunch of it, then desert farmers will never have to worry about watering their crops ever again! I. AM. A. GENIUS!

quests.name: Feathered Frenzy
quests.description: I'm sorry Hunter... Those Buddies heard that there were "ghosts" at the Shrine Ruins and ran off. I'm so worried about them with that Aknosom around. Can you hunt it while I go look for them!?

quests.name: Supply Run
quests.description: HELP! My supplier was ambushed by monsters, and dropped all their cargo on the way back to Kamura! It was near the Shrine Ruins—here, I'll mark it on your map, so can you get those ingredients back? Pleeease!?

quests.name: Faceless Foe
quests.description: Gross! There I was, taking a rest, when something wet dripped on my shoulder. I look up and—EW! Wrinkles, veins, and—ICK—a pale monster with no face that looks like a— *gag* Go hunt it PLEASE!

quests.name: The Cactus Diet
quests.description: This cactus diet has taken over my life. Cactus salad, cactus steak, cactus smoothies— you name it! But now I'm all out of Bauble Cactuses... Cacti? Whatever! Just go get me some!

quests.name: A Sandy Cabal
quests.description: What a twist! I was attacked by some strange barking creatures, but in my desperation to escape, I could not clearly identify my assailants... Hunter, please, help me solve this riddle!
quests.objective: Slay a total of 14 Jaggi or Jaggia

quests.name: Breath of the Past
quests.description: Do you know of Simple Prisms? They call it a prism, but it's really a small animal fossil. That's what Father said. I've never seen a fossil, so I'd like to take a look at it. Please find one for me.

quests.name: Ladies of the Lake
quests.description: I was looking for my lost husband in the Flooded Forest when I was attacked. I had heard tales of sirens dressed in yellow in the waters there. If I am to ever find my husband, I will need them gone.

quests.name: Infernal Lacrimosa
quests.description: I was tasked to hunt a so-called "Mermaid Dragon," in the Frost Islands. Upon arriving, I heard what sounded like a song and instantly fell asleep. I woke up back at camp covered in gashes and cuts. What happened out there!?

quests.name: Raging White-out
quests.description: The area surrounding the Frost Islands is scarce in food as it is and now a Barioth has been spotted in the area. Surely we will starve if this nuisance isn't dealt with!

quests.name: The Queen's Procession
quests.description: Woohoo! Ohhh man! The queen of the Sandy Plains is spewing fire everywhere! She burned all my stuff—even set my pants on fire, too! Haha! Wait...that's not funny... *ahem* Please hunt that Rathian!

quests.name: Streaking Shadow
quests.description: I was out exploring in the Flooded Forest, when suddenly, lightning struck. I looked to the sky and saw something zipping and zapping from tree to tree! I got away some- how, but others might not be so lucky. Please, do something!

quests.name: A Song of Red and Fire
quests.description: Can you hear that? The perfect melody of flowing lava, smoldering ash, and the bassy rumblings of the volcano all accompanied by the sound of Volvidon rolling around. Bravo! BRAVO!

quests.name: Off Your Rocker
quests.description: Dude... I'm freaking out. Every time I go to the Lava Caverns, I keep hearing this creepy voice. Like, I look around, and no one is there! No one! Uh, can you go and check it out for me? I know I'm not crazy!

quests.name: Monkey Wrench in Your Plans
quests.description: In order to separate Magnamalo from the Rampage, I need to complete my device. In order to do that, I need materials from a Bishaten. One has been spotted in the Shrine Ruins. Depart at once!

quests.name: Getting Back the Groceries
quests.description: I was cutting through the Lava Caverns one night when, out of nowhere, there was this SPOOKY roar! I freaked, dropped all my ingredients, and now...I'm way too scared to go back for them. Can you, um, go instead?

quests.name: A Poisonous Project
quests.description: My research is everything to me! And this new antidote research shall be my legacy! In order to continue my work, I'll need you to fetch me a Pukei-Pukei specimen. But you'll need to bring your own antidotes...

quests.name: Deliver the Liver
quests.description: Me and my pals are having a few drinks tonight, and we're hankerin' after some monster liver with 'em. Thing is, it's ONLY good when it's raw—and I ain't eating raw liver if it ain't fresh! Think you can hook us up?

quests.name: So Hot, It Melts Iron
quests.description: Where I'm from, if you want to make good equipment, ya gotta use lots of Coal. Maybe Kamura has some fancy pants way of doing it without coal, but we ain't got the facilities like you folks do here. Can you go get me some?

quests.name: THE BEST Quest
quests.description: My daddy's THE BEST and I want to make THE BEST gloves for him. Mommy says that Rachnoid thread is THE BEST for making gloves so... Can you go and fight a few for me and bring me the thread? You'd be THE BEST if you did!

quests.name: Third Wheel
quests.description: "In the right corner, Arzuros! And in the left corner, Tetranadon!" Oh! You're here too!? Uh... "In the middle, you!" How's that? Yeah, uh, good luck! Hope you win!

quests.name: Wind Speed Wyvern
quests.description: Nargacuga are so cool, right? And fast too! How is it that they are so light on their feet!? I MUST know! I bet if I made some Nargacuga shoes I could be just as fast as they are!

quests.name: Electrifying Ephiphany
quests.description: During a survey of the Shrine Ruins, I was struck by a bolt of lightning. At first, I thought perhaps some genius idea had come to fruition, but alas it was only a Zinogre...

quests.name: Nocturnal Tracker
quests.description: The Plains at night are quite elegant and inspiring... But someone or someTHING is following me. I feel so afraid that all my ideas and emotions are simply swept away! Please get rid of this stalker!

quests.name: Waltzing by Moonlight
quests.description: O, how elegantly the Mizutsune steps, arcing through the air... It must be the fin! If I had one for my own, surely I could dance as it does too... I know! Hunter! Waltz with the wyvern, and I shall seize its fin!

quests.name: Rathalos Alert!
quests.description: [REPORT BEGINS] Rathalos spotted in the Lava Caverns [STOP] Requesting support from all qualified hunters [STOP] Look out for the rain of fire from the sky [REPORT ENDS]

quests.name: Comeuppance
quests.description: Durin' the Rampage fifty years ago, Magnamalo showed up and caused an epic mess. We can't let that happen ever again. You gotta take down Magnamalo! Now go get to it!

quests.name: The Secret Ingredient
quests.description: So my idea is to make these new Bunny Dango that'll refresh you just like a power nap would. But to do that, I need you to capture a Somnacanth so I can use its song to make a recipe! I love you and please!

quests.name: BZZZZZ or ZZZZzzzz
quests.description: My boyfriend is straight trippin'. He thinks that Somnacanth are cuter than Khezu. HELLO! Obviously Khezu are but he won't budge. Well, if he won't see it my way, then I guess we'll let you settle this!
quests.objective: Hunt a Khezu and a Somnacanth

quests.name: Nosey Nuisances
quests.description: These monsters are so annoying! First it was that bird-brain trying to peck me to death, then it was that pink snozz-o-saurus trying to blow mucus all over me. Wish those two would keep their noses out of my business! ARGH!
quests.objective: Hunt a Kulu-Ya-Ku and an Anjanath

quests.name: The Hottest Around
quests.description: A Volvidon rammed into a Tetranadon! I don't know what they were fighting over, but it was amazing! Until they came rolling my way and almost turned me into roadkill! Leave me outta this, will ya!
quests.objective: Hunt a Tetranadon and a Volvidon

quests.name: Hermit of the Swamp
quests.description: An Almudron is makin' a real mess of things in the Shrine Ruins. They usually just keep to themselves up in the mountains... Could just be another effect of the Rampage Either way, we can't let it get any closer to the village. Now get to it!

quests.name: Abominable Snow-beast
quests.description: A monster in the Frost Islands has been roaring after dark. The cries have terrified my child, who now refuses to go to the toilet alone at night! Please, help us if you can!

quests.name: Thundering Voice
quests.description: I hear roars echoing all over, no idea where they come from. I fear it might be a Tigrex! Wherever I hide, the growling follows. Please, I beg of you... Hunt the source of that sound before it catches up with me!

quests.name: Twisted Desire
quests.description: Those horns are so cool! Fit for a name like "Diablos" for sure, with that twisted shape. I'd love to get my hands on one and craft my store sign from it. I bet it'd do wonders for business!

quests.name: A Test of Courage
quests.description: I'm no scaredy cat but the Shrine Ruins are haunted! HAUNTED, I tell ya! There was this big scary shadow with fireballs all around it and a ghost glowing in the distance surround by souls! Even meow I get chills just thinking about it! HELP!

quests.name: Like a Flash of Lightning
quests.description: Here's a favor for ya, rookie, from me. There's a Mizutsune and a Tobi-Kadachi dukin' it out in the Flooded Forest, and I'm lettin' YOU have at 'em! I'm feelin', uh...charitable today. Y-Yeah. Well, good luck!
quests.objective: Hunt a Tobi-Kadachi and a Mizutsune

quests.name: King of the Sky, Bane of the Land
quests.description: My subordinates had enough of their harsh missions and rebelled. I was forced to take responsibility and demoted to the Lava Caverns. I need to get better at my job, but to do so I need to survive first! Help!
quests.objective: Hunt a Rathalos and a Tigrex

quests.name: Advanced: The Veterans' Gala
quests.description: A Rajang, a Bazelgeuse, and Magnamalo all waitin' for ya in the Arena! Sky's the limit if you can outdo this trio. So aim sky-high, Squirt! Bwahaha!

quests.name: Shady Monster
quests.description: SAy tHeRe, hUNter~ eVEr sEeN A mOnSTeR tHAt hOPs oN One lEg? i hAvE...aND i'Ve nEveR bEen tHe sAMe sINcE—Hahaha! *hack* Those old ghost stories don't scare me none. HOW ABOUT YOU!?

quests.name: Tired and Feathered
quests.description: Thinks he's number one, does he? Just because he snatched my Gold Gargwa Egg? Well, you're gonna show him. You got that!? I'm number one around here. I'M NUMBER ONE!

quests.name: Jumped in the Frost Islands
quests.description: Psst! Hey, pal. I just got ruffed up by a gang of Izuchi and their "great" bozo leader. They took my pouch, my zenny—even my pants! Think ya could do me a solid and take care of 'em for me? And maybe, uh, get me some pants too, huh?

quests.name: No Cure for the Common Baggi
quests.description: YUCK! Fur-st a Great Baggi *sniff* spits all over me! *sniff* THEN I fall asleep out in the Frost Islands, and now *sniff* I think I'm coming down with something! Nya...Nya... *sniff* Nya...NYACHOO! *sniff*

quests.name: A Snowball's Chance...
quests.description: I absolutely cannot believe how awful my luck is. No way that thing could've hit me! There I was...bobbing...weaving. Zigging...zagging. Just when I thought I had gotten away from this Lagombi *BAM* me and all my goods crushed by a snowball. Unbelievable...

quests.name: Wroggi Place, Wroggi Time
quests.description: I was out on my morning jog through the Ruins and out pops a Great Wroggi spittin' poison all over my new running shoes. What is wrong with these monsters!? Hunter, please avenge my shoes, would you?

quests.name: A Grizzly Encounter
quests.description: What are we gonna do, Hunter? WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO!? An Arzuros attacked the latest delivery of honey into Kamura and now there are no sweets— WHAT!? Who cares if they are OK! Did you hear me? NO SWEETS!

quests.name: Off the Beaten Path
quests.description: My friend and I heard about this amazing secret spot up in the Shrine Ruins where you can relax and watch the Torchbugs glow. We wanted to take a hike up there and check it out, but there's a bunch of monsters in the way...
quests.objective: Slay a total of 20 Izuchi or Altaroth

quests.name: Hot Topic Hooligans
quests.description: I heard from my brother's mother's cousin that the Frost Islands are crawling with monsters these days. And get this, my mailman's uncle was just ruffed up out there the other day. It used to be such a nice place. Wish someone'd do something about it...
quests.objective: Slay a total of 20 Zamite or Bnahabra

quests.name: I Want Off This Ride
quests.description: I was coming home FUR-OM WORK when suddenly I SAW A BISHATEN spinning on its TAIL AND SUDDENLY it started spinning AROUND ME! Then everything STARTED SPINNING! And then I started SPINNING! AND meow I can't stop! PLEASE HELP!

quests.name: Way of the Pukei
quests.description: Master Utsushi does those monster impressions, right? Maybe if I, like, learned one, we'd have something in common. I bet I could do Pukei-Pukei. Seems easy. I'm already pretty good at sticking out my tongue. If you hunt one for me, I can watch and take notes!

quests.name: The Flooding Flooded Forest
quests.description: It's utter chaos! Our couriers are under attack from a Royal Ludroth and its mates! "Mates" as in females, by the way, not frie—wait, that doesn't even— Look, we just need you to hunt that Royal Ludroth ASAP!

quests.name: So Muddy Hardheaded!
quests.description: "You're so hardheaded, you'd put a Barroth to shame!" Heh, can you believe my wife said that to me? She thinks my head's harder than a Barroth's! There's no way! So I'm goin' out to get me a Barroth skull to prove it! And ain't no one gonna change my mind!

quests.name: A Pale Shadow
quests.description: "So...so...cold... Whiskers fur-ozen... Tail fur-ozen... Paws— Wha...What's that? A fur-iendly smile? So...warm...meow... Everything...warm—" (The diary ends there. You feel compelled to rescue its owner.)

quests.name: Reinventing the Wheel
quests.description: Wheels get stuck in the sand, limiting trade across deserts; and yet, Volvidon traverse the Plains with ease—wait, that's it! Allow me to observe how a Volvidon rolls, and I shall design an unstoppable wheel!

quests.name: Blasted Basarios!
quests.description: *cough* Dang Basarios! *wheeze* One minute you're sittin' on what you thought was a rock, tryin' to get the dirt out of yer boots, *hack* and the next, you're huffin' *cough* all kinds of who-knows-what! *hack*

quests.name: The Path to Royalty
quests.description: Oh, what I wouldn't give to be a queen! "Queen of the Land"? Who wouldn't love a title like that!? Perhaps I may learn a thing or two from the queen herself! Valiant Knight of Kamura! I order you to hunt a Rathian!

quests.name: Dead Ringer
quests.description: Me and my big mouth... I saw a picture of a Tetranadon and blurted out "It looks exactly like Master Hojo!" He overheard me and now he thinks I was talking about a Mizutsune! If he finds out the truth, he'll croak!

quests.name: The Rampage Approaches
quests.description: Well then, Hunter, the Rampage is nearing Kamura. The villages will defend the areas surrounding the Stronghold, while you fend off any monsters that make it in. Johoho! Good luck!

quests.name: Dawn of the Kestodon
quests.description: What do I do? WHAT DO I DO!? There's Kestodon all around me! Here, there, yonder, whither— they're everywhere, I tell ya, EVERYWHERE! Even in my mind! There's nowhere left to run! You gotta stop 'em before it's too late!

quests.name: Hide, Hide, Hide!
quests.description: Darling, a special order has come in for a very special client and I'm all out of materials. Be a dear and fetch some for me, will you? Only the finest materials will do. None of that faux nonsense! Now, off you go!
quests.objective: Slay a total of 20 Jagras or Ludroth

quests.name: Bouncing Brawlers
quests.description: I haven't slept in days and it's all because of those two stupid monsters. Fighting all day... Fighting all night! They never let up! The roaring. The rumbling. I can't take it anymore! Please, I need some sleep! SHUT THEM UP!
quests.objective: Hunt a Lagombi and a Tetranadon

quests.name: Fried and Baptized
quests.description: I tend to ignore these little "tiffs" between monsters while out in the field. Especially since I have a special cloak to protect me. But it becomes increasingly difficult to ignore when the forest is flooding and burning at the same time...
quests.objective: Hunt a Royal Ludroth and a Rathian

quests.name: Beckoning Slumber
quests.description: I've been suffering from insomnia... So I figured, hey, why don't I create a sedative using Somnacanth powder? At this point, I don't care how crazy it sounds. Just get me that powder, please.

quests.name: The Blizzard Blender
quests.description: Yo, I heard those Goss Harag's can turn their arms into these sick ice blades that'll carve a hunter up like, "Shwa! Shwa! Shwashwashwa SHWA!" Dude, I gotta see it! Come on, go pick a fight with one! Just, uh, don't get all "shwa-shwa-shwa"-ed up out there!

quests.name: Zigzagging Zapper
quests.description: Blargh! I was trying to hunt a stupid Tobi-Kadachi but the squirrely monster just wouldn't stay still! When I finally got an opening to strike, it scurried off and hid in a tree! Is it gonna come down anytime soon? You know what? I'm outta here! I don't got all day for this!

quests.name: Down 'n' Dirty
quests.description: Doggone Almudron! That thing came through the farm slingin' its mud all over the dern place. Now there's mud all over my dern crops. All in my dern house. Heck, even got mud in my dern pants! Well, least the Poogies is happy...

quests.name: Bully of the Caverns
quests.description: I can see why that Anjanath likes to bully all those little monsters. Them Raths always pickin' on 'em for having those li'l stubby "wings" and a funny lookin' schnoz. But that don't make it right. I don't like bullies. And I won't have any of it!

quests.name: Twilit Twin Stars
quests.description: It was a quiet night in the Ruins; that's when I saw two red stars glowing in the darkness. I felt a gust of wind, and the next thing I knew, I awoke on a hospital bed. I did not know such frightening things exist out there...

quests.name: My Muse the Mizutsune
quests.description: My husband is one of those artsy- fartsy types, you know the kind. Sees a sunset...cries. Well, he heard Mizutsune are "creatures that inspire creativity" so he ran off with his easel to find one. *sigh* Can you go save him for me?

quests.name: Champion of the Caverns
quests.description: Meow, I've seen my share of Raths before. Never thought they were that tough, just fly around and yowl at ya. Mewboy, I was so wrong... I got the big idea to take one on, paw-to-claw, and it one only took one fireball for me to hightail it out of there! Youch!

quests.name: White Knight vs. Hunter
quests.description: I am a warrior, roaming these lands to hone my skills. I've come to the Islands to observe the so-called "White Knight." I long to challenge it, however, it is custom in my country to allow you the honor first. Have at it, brave Hunter!

quests.name: Wavering Moon and Thunder
quests.description: My guards have turned craven after hearing of a Zinogre in the area. Nonetheless, I must press on through the Forest, no matter what... Which is why I implore you, brave Hunter, to vanquish the beast instead.

quests.name: A Friend in Need
quests.description: My Popo, Posey, is my best friend. She helps me every day and is the sweetest companion I've ever had. A Tigrex was spotted along my trade route and you know what they do to Popo... Hunter, please. I can't lose Posey. If I lose her, I lose everything!

quests.name: A Few Bumps Along the Way
quests.description: A buddy of mine told me about this "great shortcut" he found. The road was so bumpy I fell off my cart right into a cactus patch. And to make matters worse, a Diablos appeared out of nowhere and turned my cart into splinters... Why do these things always happen to me!?

quests.name: Hellfire
quests.description: That dreadful Magnamalo has been spotted! Quick, Hunter, you must leap into action at once! We cannot allow it to feed on the hordes or it may become too powerful to defeat! No time to waste! Hop to it-to it!

quests.name: Tail to Tail
quests.description: Both Bishaten and Almudron are known for using their powerful tails when they attack. I'm collecting information on these monsters. Could you possibly assist me? I need to ascertain which tail is stronger. The one like a fist, or the one like a whip?
quests.objective: Hunt a Bishaten and an Almudron

quests.name: Beastly Chaos
quests.description: Oh meow! A Tigrex and a Goss Harag are going berserk out in the Frost Islands! If someone doesn't stop 'em, the island's gonna get carved up like a scratching post! Help!
quests.objective: Hunt a Tigrex and a Goss Harag

quests.name: Disastrously Beautiful
quests.description: Ah. A Barroth, Tobi-Kadachi, and Magnamalo—quite the trio. Is anyone capable of dancing with three such aggressive partners, one after the other? If you intend to take to this stage, I'll be your audience.

quests.name: The Swirling Gale
quests.description: For crying out loud! I moved near the Shrine Ruins because it was a nice and quiet neighborhood... Now there's a Great Izuchi and its little gang making a ruckus. I tried to give 'em a piece of my mind but they pulled their blades on me! Hunter, please get rid of 'em!

quests.name: Divine Comedy
quests.description: You're kidding me! Why's there gotta be an Arzuros AND a Kulu-Ya-Ku on my route when I've got honey and eggs to deliver!? Is this some kind of punishment from the gods!?
quests.objective: Hunt an Arzuros and a Kulu-Ya-Ku

quests.name: Didn't Get the Memo
quests.description: I can take a Great Baggi, no problemo! But TWO!? Nobody said anything about two of 'em! I mean, maybe if I had like a heads up or something, I'd be alright. Someone should have told me! What—!? It's written in the quest description? Come on! Nobody reads that stuff!

quests.name: Dancing A-purr-ition
quests.description: Help, Hunter! I just saw this su-purr creepy umbrella monster! I tried to get close to see if it was real or if I was just i-meow-gining it and it tried to attack me! I've never been more tra-mew-tized in all my nine lives! Make it go away!

quests.name: The Frost Islands Arena
quests.description: Oh~yeah! You're going nowhere. I've got you for fifty minutes...Fifty minutes of huntin' time! Heard this Tetranadon was out there talkin' smack. You gonna stand there and take that!? Or are ya gonna go out there and put 'em in a world of hurt!?

quests.name: Even Cute Things Have Fangs
quests.description: I have this Felyne friend, and she got all scared about some big fluffy bunny. But I don't get it, 'cause bunnies are supposed to be cute! Can you go check it out so she'll stop being such a scaredy-cat?

quests.name: Night of the Khezu
quests.description: I was out fishing; everything dark and gloomy. When suddenly down flew a Khezu; slimy and gooey. Horrified to find there were no eyes that would twinkle, only a blubbery neck...veiny and wrinkled.

quests.name: Dango Duty
quests.description: I heard the Frost Islands are crawling with Izuchi and Baggi! My ingredients supplier will be passing through there and the last thing I want is for them to get pounced on by some dumb monsters! Could you maybe go and check it out, pleeeeeeease?
quests.objective: Slay a total of 20 Izuchi or Baggi

quests.name: Study the Sword & Shield
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! An Aknosom makes clever use of its big crest to fight, right? Understand how to maneuver around these kinds of attacks and you'll learn the very essence of the sword & shield!

quests.name: Totally Not Cool, Kulu!
quests.description: A pair of Kulu-Ya-Ku is after the eggs I had dibs on for my dango! No fair, AND rude! But if you can keep them occupied, I can grab the eggs before they eat 'em. You'll help me out, right? Right?

quests.name: Honing Your Hunting Horn
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! Harmonize with the sounds of nature as you serenade these monster to permanent sleep and you're sure to find a new tune for the hunting horn!
quests.objective: Hunt a Great Izuchi and Tetranadon

quests.name: Study the Switch Axe
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! The Lagombi and the Khezu may both be white but that's where their similarities end. If you can take on this contrasting pair at once, you'll discover the essence of the switch axe.
quests.objective: Hunt a Lagombi and a Khezu

quests.name: Learning the Light Bowgun
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! The path to light bowgun mastery is paved by the Great Baggi and the Great Wroggi. Their sly and agile combat is full of potential for new hit and run tactics for this weapon!
quests.objective: Hunt a Great Baggi and a Great Wroggi

quests.name: Learning the Light Bowgun
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! The path to light bowgun mastery is paved by the Great Baggi and the Great Wroggi. Their sly and agile combat is full of potential for new hit and run tactics for this weapon!
quests.objective: Hunt a Great Baggi and a Great Wroggi

quests.name: Donning Toxicity
quests.description: I've hit a bit of a slump, and I'm looking for something to rekindle my creativity. Hmm... Aha! Yes, a Great Wroggi hide! Its vivid hues make for great inspiration, and there just so happens to be one in the area!

quests.name: Lost and Found
quests.description: Oh, man... On my way home, I dropped my wallet somewhere near the Ruins. My mom's gonna be SO mad if I don't bring it back, but there're too many monsters around there to go look for it... Please help me, Hunter!
quests.objective: Slay a total of 20 Jagras or Bullfango

quests.name: Blue, Round, and Cute
quests.description: You there! Tell me, don't you think Arzuros are the cutest!? Fuzzy blue fur, a soft tubby belly; what I wouldn't give to hug 'em! Sooo, can you capture one for m— Whaddya mean, "only if I promise not to hug it?"

quests.name: Bowled Over
quests.description: Man, I cannot catch a break! I was making my way through the Plains when I started hearing this, *boingy* *boingy* *boingy* noise. Then suddenly two Volvidon appear out of nowhere and roll over my cart! To make matters worse, any produce that didn't get squashed was covered in their nasty spit!

quests.name: Rotten Fruit
quests.description: It was my fur-st time seeing a Bishaten up close. It looked so playful and fur- iendly! It even started throwing fruit to me. I thought they were purr-esents but one of them blinded me with a flash and the other zapped my tail! What a meanie! Go teach it a lesson fur me!

quests.name: Rise above the Mud
quests.description: Aaaargh! I was SO close! *sigh* Right as I was about to land the final blow on a Barroth, my feet got stuck in some mud! Not only did it proceed to stomp the crap out of me, but then it got away! Once I'm better—*ouch* I'm gonna go and finish what I started!

quests.name: Go Away, Pukei!
quests.description: I am absolutely fuming right now! I spent months, MONTHS, breaking my back to have a good harvest this year, and it takes only one day for that googly-eyed monster to wipe out all my crops. Think you can go harvest its hide for me?

quests.name: Miner Problem
quests.description: Had a new guy on the team get pretty messed up by a Basarios. He came across a boulder juttin' up out of the ground and thought he hit the jackpot. Poor kid didn't know what he was doing when he planted a pickaxe square in the monster's rocky rear.

quests.name: Foul Play in the Forest
quests.description: Hey, listen here. Don't go tellin' people what I'm about to tell you, capiche? Some of our "special ingredients" come from the Flooded Forest, but now some rivals are tryin' to move in on our turf. This is not good for business. And, we can't have that, can we?

quests.name: Charmed by a Queen
quests.description: Hunter Hunter HUNTER! We must go at once! As we speak the queen herself is gracing the Shrine Ruins! I must capture her majesty in all its glory! But I hear Rathian are rather... difficult to work with. Perhaps you can assist me?

quests.name: Grasp the Great Sword
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! The Bishaten may move and attack in its own unique way, but when it hits big, it hits BIG! See for yourself what I mean, and you'll definitely find new ways to swing a great sword!

quests.name: Honing Your Hammer
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! The secret to hammer— Well, let's not kid ourselves here... Hammer equals thrashing and pummeling your target. Go hunt this Pukei-Pukei and Barroth and you'll know exactly what I mean!
quests.objective: Hunt a Pukei-Pukei and a Barroth

quests.name: Learn the Lance
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! A knight wields their lance to protect the weak—just like a Rathian fiercely protects her young! Capture the queen and you'll acquire some new Skills for your lance!

quests.name: Charge Blade Coalescing
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! Like the Royal Ludroth and Jyuratodus, you'll need to be in water—Wait, no... You'll need to be "AS water." Meaning you'll have to be flexible according to the situation. Understanding this is the key to unlocking the charge blade's potential!
quests.objective: Hunt a Royal Ludroth and a Jyuratodus

quests.name: Hone Your Heavy Bowgun
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! Strategically strike from a distance like the Volvidon, or get up close and personal like a Basarios. Add their fighting styles to the long-range, high-powered heavy bowgun, and you should learn something new!
quests.objective: Hunt a Basarios and a Volvidon

quests.name: Bad Review
quests.description: I just got done talking to my best friend and her neighbor's daughter had THE WORST experience out in the Sandy Plains. Apparently, the locals were extremely rude and wouldn't stop butting in to her business. The nerve...
quests.objective: Slay a total of 20 Rhenoplos or Kestodon

quests.name: Flooded Forest Fiasco
quests.description: *sniff* Papa promised we'd go fishin' 'cuz I was a good boy, I did all my chores. Brushed my teeth. Even cleaned my room! But now we can't *sniff* because *sniff* a bunch of dumb monsters. *sob* It's not fair! *sniff*
quests.objective: Slay a total of 20 Ludroth or Wroggi

quests.name: The Restless Swamp
quests.description: One of our scouts tracking a Jyuratodus has gone missing in the Flooded Forest. If you would hunt the beast so that it is safe enough to dispatch a search party, it would be much appreciated. Now, hop to it-to it!

quests.name: Shadows Over the Frost
quests.description: It has come to the board's attention that one of our members has not returned from the Frost Islands. We have to assume that the trader must have been attacked thus we are requiring the assistance of a hunter. We will send out a rescue team (or cleap-up crew) once you have completed your task.
quests.objective: Hunt a Khezu and a Tetranadon

quests.name: Skies Flash, Clouds Boom
quests.description: Eep! WH-WHAT WAS THAT!? Don't sneak up on me, Hunter! I-I've been on edge ever since a Zinogre j-jumped out on me! Brr...my fur's still on end from the fear...a-and static! Could y-you help me-me-meow-t?

quests.name: A Somniferous Elegy
quests.description: Had a group of travelers come in last night fleeing a Somnacanth. Dang monster must have got 'em good because they're still sleepin'! I can't have guests stayin' past check out time! Hunter, can ya go do something 'bout that thing?

quests.name: Sharpening Amber Fangs
quests.description: My boyfriend's on his way here for my birthday. Oh, thank you! Anyway, he'll be passing through the Frost Islands to get here and I just heard that a Barioth has been spotted! Hunter, I didn't get all dolled up for nothing! You gotta get rid of it so he (and his presents) arrive safely!

quests.name: Closer Than it Appears
quests.description: I was en route to do some business when I started hearing this stomping noise behind me. It was faint at first, but then started getting louder and louder! I turn around and there's an Anjanath right behind me! I've never screamed and run so hard in my life!

quests.name: The Abyss Stares Back
quests.description: I still see it. Even now when I close my eyes. A moving void. The darkest dark you could ever imagine. You don't even know it's there until it's too late. From the abyss of night, two streaks of red surge towards you. Before you can even react, it has you.

quests.name: Red Skies at Night
quests.description: I saw it one night: a stunning firework rising up above the Caverns, so bright, the night looked like day. If that was the doing of a monster, it's got to be a pro at using fire. I need to know what it was.

quests.name: Skies are Gray
quests.description: When the skies cloud over, ya think there's rain on the way, don'tcha? Well, this time, it weren't no storm, it was a dang Tobi-Kadachi! Can't do no fishin' when you're gettin' zapped in the rear every other minute! I want that varmint gone, ya hear me!?

quests.name: Do It for the Dango!
quests.description: Grrrr! Stupid. Monsters. Everywhere! Why won't they leave me alone? I go to one fishing spot—Monster. I go to a different spot—ANOTHER MONSTER. Why are they so rude!? Can you go let those meanies know just how mad I am!?
quests.objective: Hunt a Nargacuga and a Jyuratodus

quests.name: A Bewitching Dance
quests.description: Ah, . A Mizutsune has become quite aggressive in the Shrine Ruins. They're normally not like this— What could have caused it to go hopping mad!? We'll investigate while you take care of it.

quests.name: Learn the Long Sword
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! Sharp, flowing strikes are the soul of long sword combat. The fearlessness of a Zinogre and the elegance of a Mizutsune combined are just the thing you'll need to master 'em!
quests.objective: Hunt a Zinogre and a Mizutsune

quests.name: Grasp the Gunlance
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! Getting in your target's face and remaining calm is the key to unleashing the true potential of the gunlance. And no monster teaches "in-your-face" better than the Barioth!

quests.name: Dissect the Dual Blades
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! Fending off an Anjanath and a Rathian at the same time may sound crazy, but it's just the challenge for any hunter who's looking to develop their dual blade technique!
quests.objective: Hunt an Anjanath and a Rathian

quests.name: Be One with the Bow
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! Speed, agility, and positioning are the signatures of the Tobi- Kadachi. Have you ever noticed how similar they are to the bow? Well, now you know, go see it for yourself!

quests.name: Invoke the Insect Glaive
quests.description: Alright, Ace, lesson time! Swift, graceful, dance-like: that sounds like the attacks of a Somnacanth, an Aknosom, and an insect glaive, right? Try combining the three, and see what you end up learning!
quests.objective: Hunt a Somnacanth and an Aknosom

quests.name: The Lava Caverns Sweep
quests.description: A great horde of monsters has gathered in the Lava Caverns, but I must pass through! My guards and I cannot defeat them, I know this—but I also know that a hunter as skilled as you can. Will you help us?
quests.objective: Slay a total of 20 Uroktor or Rachnoid

quests.name: Showdown in the Arena
quests.description: Gather 'round, gather 'round! Today we have a show packed with fur and fury! Anjanath! Mizutsune! Zinogre! Sparks will fly! Fire will burn! Bubbles— d-does that say bubbles? It does. Uh... OK. Bubbles will, um, bubble! Who dares challenge this trifecta of trepidation!

quests.name: Serpent God of Wind
quests.description: Hunter, the Rampage approaches, roused by the Wind Serpent. Our village defenders will target Ibushi and lure it out to the Stronghold, where you'll be waiting. And then it's all up to you. Johoho! We're counting on you, now!

quests.name: It's Gonna Get You!
quests.description: Mom always says, "If you don't behave, the snow demon from the Frost Islands is gonna come and gobble you up!" Yeah, right! There's no snow demon out there! ...Is there? Uh, on second thought, maybe you could go check for me?

quests.name: Clad in Hellfire
quests.description: What an embarrassment. My best armor was about as effective as wet paper against Magnamalo. I tell ya, that hellfire is a one-way ticket back to camp... I guess I need to hit up the Smithy again. Think you can finish up the quest for me?

quests.name: Subterranean Disturbances
quests.description: We've recently been getting earthquakes, as if something is shuffling beneath our feet. Everyone's scared and rightly so! It's hard enough trying to keep it together when we can barely keep things on the shelves!

quests.name: A Muddy Invitation
quests.description: Just look at me... Yuck! Covered from head to tail in mud. Meow I have to take a bath with Meowster... And you know Felynes hate baths! Can you go take care of that nasty creature while I go scrub Meowster's back?

quests.name: A Resounding Roar
quests.description: Did you hear that? It was that Tigrex! That monster's invaded the Plains and has been hollerin' up a storm ever since. Now all our Popo are spooked and won't budge. Can't blame 'em...they are a Tigrex's favorite snack. Please, Hunter. You gotta help us out!

quests.name: Evil Afoot
quests.description: A d-d-demon, I tell you! A demon! No one's safe with that thing around! No one! The Felynes, the dango, the twins—ME! Oh my Gog! ME! I'm not safe! AHHHHHH! Hunter! What are you doing!? Go get rid of that thing!

quests.name: Can't Kill It with Fire
quests.description: Rakna-Kadaki inhabit a select few regions, and yet one has just been sighted in the Lava Caverns... I just don't get it-get it! All of this strange activity around the region. And now Minoto is acting strange as well...

quests.name: Serpent Goddess of Thunder
quests.description: At last! The chance to end this miserable calamity is at hand! You must defeat Thunder Serpent Narwa once and for all! Hunter of Kamura, go and be victorious! I and the rest of your family are awaiting your triumphant return!

quests.name: Seared Situation
quests.description: Bunny Dango slow-cooked over lava: sounds super yummy, right!? I was gonna go out to the Lava Caverns to try it out... WAS until I heard there was a Rathalos and Magnamalo. How rude! Could you go get rid of them please!?

quests.name: Ruckus in the Ruins
quests.description: Whoa! It is TOTALLY going down right now in the Shrine Ruins! One minute there's mud everywhere. Then the next, there's bubbles everywhere. Mud. Bubbles. Mud! Bubbles! I think you need to go out and clean up this mess!
quests.objective: Hunt an Almudron and a Mizutsune

quests.name: A Quartet of Horns
quests.description: UGH! I was gathering herbs for my new menu out in the Sandy Plains, and guess what? Two dumb Diablos showed up to stab my lunch dango on their horns! Grr, I want payback on those jerks!

quests.name: Occupational Hazards
quests.description: I love when monsters keep destroying my carts and my livelihood—said no trader ever! First a Lagombi, then a Diablos, then two Volvidon, and NOW a Rajang and Zinogre! I just want, for once, to get from point A to point B without getting beat up by monsters!
quests.objective: Hunt a Rajang and a Zinogre

quests.name: Omnidirectional Threats
quests.description: Hi, I'd like to speak to whoever is in charge here. Yes, I heard that there were two monsters in the Lava Caverns. This is completely unacceptable! If something is not done about this right away, I WILL be contacting the guild to file a complaint!
quests.objective: Hunt a Rakna-Kadaki and a Khezu

quests.name: A Frosty Stalemate
quests.description: Hey, um, sorry to interrupt you, but I think there's something out in the Frost Islands that "may" need your attention. These two monsters have been going at it for a while now and it seems to be getting worse. Just, uh, thought you should know.
quests.objective: Hunt a Goss Harag and a Tetranadon

quests.name: Fought, Failed, Fired Up
quests.description: *sigh* I took on a Diablos and failed... I took on an Anjanath—failed. I just can't anymore. How can it even be done? You've challenged all sorts of beasts, surely these are nothing to you. Maybe if I watch you defeat them, it'll rekindle the fire inside me.
quests.objective: Hunt a Diablos and an Anjanath

quests.name: A Whirlwind of a Stage
quests.description: I've been suffering from a severe case of writer's block, so I asked an acquaintance of mine to set up a grand stage performance. All you have to do, Hunter, is play your part, and surely I will find the inspiration I need to finish my romance novel!

quests.name: Ancient Illusion
quests.description: A Chameleos has shown itself— hmmm...no. A Chameleos has appeared—*sigh* A Chameleos has been spot—We know it's out there! Go hunt the cursed thing before it unleashes toadal chaos! Now, hop to it-to it!

quests.name: The Steely Storm
quests.description: Johoho! This quest will just "blow" your socks off, Hunter! *ahem* Pardon me! The Kushala Daora is an elder dragon shrouded in mystery. How they are able to summon tempests simply, joho, "blows" our mind! Johoho! *ahem*

quests.name: The Emperor of Flame
quests.description: A Teostra has been spotted in the Lava Caverns. Wreathed in flame, Teostra are of such a fierce and deadly nature that the Guild keeps track of their movements whenever possible. You must leap into action at once and extinguish this threat!

quests.name: A Blaze Among Beasts
quests.description: Got a real challenge here for ya, Squirt! Bwahaha! Look at those ears perk up! I knew it'd be right up your alley! Best these beasties and ol' Fugen will give ya a new Petalace. Sounds good, don't it!? Now go get to it!

quests.name: Death From Above
quests.description: I've never seen anything like it! From the skies I heard a distant roar and then "it" came. Like hell falling from the heavens, fire rained down, scorching the earth. Time almost stood still as everything around me was consumed by flame.

quests.name: May Fire Quell Fury
quests.description: Bein' flexible in any situation's the mark of a true hunter, and I've got just the quest to test ya! If you can capture me a Rajang, you pass—and ya get yourself a new Petalace too! Now, go get to it!

quests.name: Return of the Bazelgeuse
quests.description: That cursed thing has returned! And with it, fire and destruction! Where it will strike next, we do not know. All we can do is follow the trail of devastation it has left behind. Hunter we ask that you stop this terror from the skies!

quests.name: Return of the Bazelgeuse
quests.description: That cursed thing has returned! And with it, fire and destruction! Where it will strike next, we do not know. All we can do is follow the trail of devastation it has left behind. Hunter we ask that you stop this terror from the skies!

quests.name: The Avaricious Apex Arzuros
quests.description: I've spent a lot time hiking through the Ruins and I've seen more than my share of Arzuros... But the one I saw earlier was no ordinary Arzuros. I think this one was of those Apex monsters I've heard about. And if it was I won't be taking any more hiking trips through the Ruins anytime soon.

quests.name: The Graceful Apex Rathian
quests.description: I TOTALLY thought that Rathian was 'bout done for, 'cause it looked like, SUPER beat up. But then it got mad, and it was, like, soooo STRONG! Like, what even is its problem, y'know? Anyway, can you hunt it for me? Thaaanks!

quests.name: The Harlequin Apex Mizutsune
quests.description: Good evening, Master Hunter. I hate to disturb you in this late hour, but I have received word that an Apex Mizutsune was spotted along my employer's route home. I ask that you guarantee his safe return.

quests.name: The Fearsome Apex Rathalos
quests.description: Talk about a bad fur day! Just when my tail healed up, I come across an even meaner Rathalos! An Apex one, too! As soon as it spotted me it barfed up this meowssive fireball! At this point, the fur on my tail will never grow back...

quests.name: Master Utsushi's Challenge Part 1
quests.description: Yo, Ace! You've been making some totally gnarly progress recently! Does a man good to see his pupil train so hard! In fact, let's kick it up a notch! Got just the quest for you, and it's a real banger!

quests.name: Master Utsushi's Challenge Part 3
quests.description: Yo, Ace! You've been making some totally gnarly progress recently! Does a man good to see his pupil train so hard! In fact, let's kick this up a notch! Got just the quest for you, and it's a real banger!

quests.name: Arena 01
quests.description: Yo, Ace! Ready for some awesome Arena action!? Prove your mettle using the equipment provided here!

quests.name: The Allmother
quests.description: Ibushi and Narwa have convened at the Coral Palace—that means we're running out of time... You must give them both the paddling of their lives, and break the chains shackling our village!

quests.name: The Evil Star from Beyond
quests.description: The Valstrax has returned. If you plan on takin' it on, beware its wings! If they don;t burn you to a crisp, they'll dang sure poke you pull of holes. Be quick and stay on your toes out there! Got it? Well, good luck to ya!

quests.name: The Devastating Apex Diablos
quests.description: I saw it! I saw that terrifying—Wait... What was it I saw? A three-eyed goat? No... A beady-eyed ghost? Dern it! OH! It was a Diablos! But it wasn't a Diablos...know what I mean? No...? Well, it had horns...And... Well, shoot. I forget... Just go hunt the dang thing!

quests.name: The Voltaic Apex Zinogre
quests.description: I was out on patrol in the Ruins, when suddenly, lightning struck all around me. I thought perhaps I had angered the gods enshrined there. But it wasn't any god, it was worse. It was a Zinogre. But this was no ordinary Zinogre. Tread carefully out there, Hunter.

quests.name: Advanced: Dual Calamities
quests.description: Magnamalo AND a Bazelgeuse!? At the SAME time!? What are we gonna do!? We're doomed I tell ya! DOOMED! There's nowhere to run! There's nowhere to hide! I'm gonna get gobbled up—No! I'm gonna get blown to bits! Maybe even both!
quests.objective: Hunt a Magnamalo and a Bazelgeuse

quests.name: Advanced: Monsters in Ink
quests.description: Hunter Hunter HUNTER! A Goss Harag, a Tigrex, and a Mizutsune are all out in the Frost Islands right at this moment! If you'd be willing to take the three of them on, I shall observe you, painting a masterpiece of the action! It will be my finest work!
quests.objective: Hunt a Goss Harag, a Tigrex, and a Mizutsune

quests.name: Advanced: Of Storm and Fire
quests.description: Really? TWO elder dragons!? Why, this is THE observation opportunity of two lifetimes! Here: you just slay them as you would usually, while we carry out our research. Easy, right? Nothing to worry about!
quests.objective: Slay a Kushala Daora and a Teostra

quests.name: Advanced: Scaredy-Cat
quests.description: It was so scary, Hunter! I was trying to get home when I got caught in this creepy mist. It was so thick, I could barely see my whiskers! I heard a rustling noise and when I spun around, I saw it! A two-horned demon! Please! Don't let it get me!
quests.objective: Slay a Chameleos and hunt a Rajang

quests.name: Advanced: The Fallen Comet
quests.description: Oh, wow! I just saw a comet fall into the Lava Caverns! While I really wanna check it out, I'm also not trying to go there by myself. Not with all the creepy crawly things that live there. Hey, what if it wasn't a comet but that legendary elder dragon!? C'mon! Let's go!
quests.objective: Slay a Crimson Glow Valstrax and hunt a Rakna-kadaki

quests.name: The Crimson Glow
quests.description: Ancient texts speak of the Crimson Glow Valstrax as the "Scourge of the World." Well, now that it's returned, we won't let it destroy the peace that Kamura has fought so hard for! Time to hop to it-to it!

quests.name: Advanced: Proof of Power
quests.description: I. AM. PUMPED! Now that I'm a hunter, I cannot WAIT to see some action! And this quest is EXACTLY the type of action I'm looking for! Whattaya say, Hunter? Think you can best all three of these bad boys?

quests.name: Advanced: Those Crowned Apex
quests.description: Gather 'round, gather 'round! Tonight we have a grand show of magnitude and might! Apexes galore for your viewing pleasure! Mizutsune! Rathalos! Zinogre! Who will step up to the challenge!? Come one 'n' all to find out!

quests.name: Out of Sight, Out of Mind's Eye
quests.description: After the most brutal training, I have become one with the shadows and achieved enlightenment. However, a Tetranadon hinders my training. I will bestow my wisdom upon any who can defeat it.

quests.name: Arena 06
quests.description: Yo, Ace! Ready for some awesome Arena action!? Prove your mettle using the equipment provided here!
quests.objective: Slay a Volvidon, a Basarios, and a Bazelgeuse

quests.name: Challenge Quest 01
quests.description: Sup, Ace? Ready for a REAL challenge? Don't think I'm gonna go easy on ya jast 'cuz you're my favorite. Nah, it's thrash or BE thrashed! If ya know what I mean. Let's see what you got!

quests.name: Arena 03
quests.description: Yo, Ace! Ready for some awesome Arena action!? Prove your mettle using the equipment provided here!
quests.objective: Slay a Royal Ludroth and a Nargacuga

quests.name: Arena 02
quests.description: Yo, Ace! Ready for some awesome Arena action!? Prove your mettle using the equipment provided here!

quests.name: Bird Wyverns of Ruin?
quests.description: Do you know the Felyne Tsukino, who appears in the mew MONSTER HUNTER STORIES 2: WINGS OF RUIN? She's so cute! Complete this quest and I'll give you materials to gorge layered armor to make your Palico look just like her!

quests.name: Almudron: Fashion Victim
quests.description: Rondine showed me a pair of tight pants from some far off country. I don't know fashion, but I know a pair of sturdy pants when I see 'em! Complete my request, and I'll give you the materials to forge 'em.

quests.name: Fooled in the Flooded Forest
quests.description: Shhh! Don't mind me! I ran into a Chameleos and now I'm stalling for time playing possum. But I don't think I can fool it for much longer! If you can take care of it for me, I'll teach ya my trick for getting out of a bind!

quests.name: Rampage: Muddi Gras
quests.description: Ah, Hunter! Take a look at these festive stickers I made! They are so... festive! Johoho! Really put you in the mood to celebrate, do they not? Complete my request, and they're yours! Now... hop it-to it!

quests.name: Rampage: Kamura Night Hunt
quests.description: A Rampage unlike any before is hurtlin' towards the village, and that fiend Ibushi is leadin' it! Be on the lookout for Magnamalo; there's a good change it'll show up for a snack. It's up to you to protect the village! Go get to it!

quests.name: Rampage: Enchanting Parade
quests.description: Oh my Gog! Those monsters are sooooo cute! But why do they have to be so mean? *pout* If you go out and teach them to behave, I'll teach YOU a new gesture. It's my signature move so I know you'll just love it!

quests.name: USJ - Arzuros Onslaught!
quests.client: Dapper Crewmate up to No Good
quests.description: USJ presents to you a horde of Arzuros closing in like a raging tide! Ride the raging waves and claim the materials to craft Palico gear that gleams like the azure star!

quests.name: A Good old-Fashioned Rampage
quests.description: M-My goodness! All the terrors that hunters fought off in the past have shown up in this Rampage! You're a fresh-faced hunter how, but you'll go down in history if you can defeat them. And if you do, I'll give you some materials to make some layered armor!

quests.name: Rampage: Rampaging Rajang
quests.description: Attention! Rampage incoming! All hunters report to the Stronghold -- Wait wait! You! Come back here! Who taught you to run like....that!? You look like a Gargwa trying to lay an egg! Look, I gotta go warn Kamura, but if you survive this, I'll show you my running techniques.

quests.name: Heart of a Hero
quests.description: Hey, Hunter! There's a deathmatch raging on in the Arena between a teeny-tiny Tigrex and a dango-droppingly big Diablos! If you can go over and quiet that racket down. I'll give ya some new titles. Sound good? Good! Now go get to it!
quests.objective: Hunt a Tigrex and a Diablos

quests.name: Kunai Ask You a Favor?
quests.description: I have mastered the kunai! Swords? Bows? Hah! Don't need 'em! ...Well, at least, I thought I didn't until those monsters put me face down, tassets up in the a cart back to camp. Avenge my bruise behind and I'll teach you my kunai-accentuated poses!
quests.objective: Hunt a Barroth, a Rathian and a Diablos

quests.name: Apex Rathian Emergency
quests.description: Urgent notice from the Hunter's Guild: Unique Apex sighted, requesting its elimination ASAP. Monster appears to be far more dangerous than any Apex to date. Retreat if deemed too dangerous.

quests.name: Troubled Waters
quests.description: I hunt for ancient tresure that lies in the deepest rivers and oceans. Sadly, my next diving spot is swimming with monsters. Would you clear them out for me? If you o, I'll give you the materials to make some new layered armor.

quests.name: Rajang's Holiday Special
quests.description: Ah, Hunter! I have some johoho-vial news for you! After hearing tales of a distant land where they throw the merriest of parties, I was inspired to make some festive stickers! Complete my request, and they're yours! Now...hop to it-to it!

quests.name: Heart of an Apex
quests.description: Hey, Squirt! We've got reports of a buncha Apex toughies gatherin' in one spot! Now normally these baddies would put a hunter in the dirt, but my zenny's on you. Put THEM in the dirt an these Guild Card titles are yours! Bwahaha! Now go get to it!

quests.name: Apex Mizustune Emergency
quests.description: Urgent notice from the Hunter's Guild: Unique Apex sighted, requesting its elimination ASAP. Monster appears to be far more dangerous than any Apex to date. Retreat if deemed too dangerous.

quests.name: Nothing to Sneeze At!
quests.description: Ah...ah...ACHOO! Sorry... *sniff* Ugh... Caught a cold somewhere between the Frost Islands and Lava Caverns... If I'm ever gonna study Bisha...AH...ACHOOO! *sniff* Bishaten, I'll need your help. In return, I'll teach you some poses that vividly express my misery...

quests.name: Blazin' Soul of a Warrior
quests.description: They say the soul of a true warrior burns bright like a fire, blazin' a path for the next generation. Magnamalo's soul is a scorchin' inferno of hatred. Tormented by its insatiable hunger... Hunter of Kumura! Go forth and show us whose soul burns brightest!

quests.name: Apex Rathalos Emergency
quests.description: Urgent notice from the Hunter's Guild: Unique Apex sighted, requesting its elimination ASAP. Monster appears to be far more dangerous than any Apex to date. Retreat if deemed too dangerous.

quests.name: Frost Bites
quests.description: Help us! HELP US! Anyone! Our safari has been surrounded by monsters, and now we're stuck out in the cold! Good thing I wore something warm and I'll give you some materials to make your very own if you get those monsters to scram!
quests.objective: Hunt a Lagombi, a Barioth, and a Goss Harag

quests.name: Advanced: Born of Paradise
quests.description: Wind Serpent Ibushi and Thunder Serpent Narwa...in other words: the Allmother has risen once again in the Coral Palace. And judging by this existential dread I'm feeling right now, with more power than ever before... Please be careful!
quests.objective: Slay Wind Serpent Ibushi and Narwa the Allmother

quests.name: Dastardly Vile Aknosom Trio
quests.description: What's wrong, Hunter? The winter days got you feeling chilly? Well, I've got just the thing to warm your spirits! Johoho! I've made some new stickers and they're wonderfully wintery! Complete my request, and they're yours! Now...hop to it-to it!

quests.name: Apex Diablos Emergency
quests.description: Urgent notice from the Hunter's Guild: Unique Apex sighted, requesting its elimination ASAP. Monster appears to be far more dangerous than any Apex to date. Retreat if deemed too dangerous.

quests.name: Wrestling with Pain
quests.description: Ow-ow-ow... Sittin' down at work all these years has done a number on my back... Your back's gonna be busted too if you don't learn to sit right! Look at ya slouchin'! Tell you what, do this here quest and I'll teach ya all about posture!
quests.objective: Hunt an Arzuros and a Tetranadon

quests.name: USJ - Shrine Showdown!
quests.client: Dapper Crewmate up to No Good
quests.description: USJ presents to you a thrilling battle stage with a ravenous river beast, a sly mud dweller and a beast of pure malice! Leap onto the field of battle and reap materials to craft gear that gleams like the azure star!
quests.objective: Hunt a Tetranadon, an Almudron, and Magnamalo

quests.name: Advance: Crimson Calamity
quests.description: The ancient tomes say it is an evil star -- a peculiar comet that glows an ominous red. Each coming day, the crimson hue grows fiercer and soon threatens to sunder the very earth. Only you hold the power to bring down this evil from the sky.

quests.name: Princesses' Banquet
quests.description: Ah, Hunter! There's a custom in a far-off land of giving sweets to express one's feelings. I thought it was such a nice idea that I made stickers about it! If you complete my request, I'll give them to you. Now, hop to it-to it!

quests.name: Apex Zinogre Emergency
quests.description: Urgent notice from the Hunter's Guild: Unique Apex sighted, requesting its elimination ASAP. Monster appears to be far more dangerous than any Apex to date. Retreat if deemed too dangerous.

quests.name: Monster Maniacs
quests.description: I've met some crazy fans before, but these gues are foaming at the mouth to get an autograph! I know it's hard to resist my charm, but I need security to get rid of them, pronto. When they're gona, I'll teach you some super cutesy poses!
quests.objective: Hunt a Volvidon, an Anjanath and a Tigrex

quests.name: Zin an Yang
quests.description: Oh, great! JUST GREAT. Where'd that stupid paper go!? No need to panic -- why should I panic? *ahem* Could you, um, maybe take care of the quest for me? I'll give you some materials to make layered armor if you do! And... could you keep this just between us?
quests.objective: Hunt a Zinogre and a Khezu

quests.name: Heart of Might
quests.description: Hey, Squirt. We got some of the mightiest elder dragons out in the Infernal Springs. Are they too mightly for ya to brawl with? Only one way to find out. Take 'em down and I'll give ya some new titles. Sound good? Now get to it!

quests.name: The Tiniest Snowbaron!
quests.description: Ah, Hunter! Our little Komitsu asked me to illustrate some Bombadgy pictures for her. She loved them so much, I turned them into stickers! Johoho! Complete my request, and they're yours! Now...hop to it-to it!

quests.name: Memories of That Day
quests.description: (It's actually a request from a certain tailor, but it's written by Minoto...) "The reward is material for layered armor. And, uh, the armor is kind of...adorable, so...after you make it, I think I'll order another in secret..."
quests.objective: Hunt a Great Izuchi, a Mizutsune, and Magnamalo

quests.name: Super Shady Look-alike
quests.description: I thought that dumb faker was following me around again, but turns out it was something else. I'm getting real bad vibes from it. Send it packing and I'll hook you up with some materials to make some sweet layered armor!

quests.name: Challenge Quest 02
quests.description: Sup, Ace? Ready for a REAL challenge? Don't think I'm gonna go easy on ya just 'cuz you're my favorite. Nah, it's thrash or BE thrashed, if ya know what I mean. Let's see what you got!

quests.name: Challenge Quest 03
quests.description: Sup, Ace? Ready for a REAL challenge? Don't think I'm gonna go easy on ya just 'cuz you're my favorite. Nah, it's thrash or BE thrashed, if ya know what I mean. Let's see what you got!

quests.name: Challenge Quest 04
quests.description: Sup, Ace? Ready for a REAL challenge? Don't think I'm gonna go easy on ya just 'cuz you're my favorite. Nah, it's thrash or BE thrashed, if ya know what I mean. Let's see what you got!

quests.name: Challenge Quest 05
quests.description: Sup, Ace? Ready for a REAL challenge? Don't think I'm gonna go easy on ya just 'cuz you're my favorite. Nah, it's thrash or BE thrashed, if ya know what I mean. Let's see what you got!

quests.name: Challenge Quest 06
quests.description: Sup, Ace? Ready for a REAL challenge? Don't think I'm gonna go easy on ya just 'cuz you're my favorite. Nah, it's thrash or BE thrashed, if ya know what I mean. Let's see what you got!
quests.objective: Slay a Somnacanth, a Goss Harag, and Magnamalo

quests.name: Challenge Quest 07
quests.description: Sup, Ace? Ready for a REAL challenge? Don't think I'm gonna go easy on ya just 'cuz you're my favorite. Nah, it's thrash or BE thrashed, if ya know what I mean. Let's see what you got!

quests.name: An Icy Blade So Bright
quests.description: I just don't understand young hunters and their "fashion"... Some of them even paint their glasses solid black! It boggles the mind! Well, if this sort of thing interests you, complete my request and I'll give you the materials to make them.

quests.name: SF: Ultimate Promotion Exam
quests.description: Looking to train with the best, I see! Well, you came to the right place! My prized pupil is -- Hold on, there's two of 'em!? And the second one has a dark aura!? *shrug* Anyway, you just need to defeat one!

quests.name: White Desert Blossom
quests.description: Ah, Hunter! You can always count on endemic life to help you on hunts! And if you complete my request, johoho, you can count on them to help communicate with your friends! Hop to it-to it and these stickers are yours!

quests.name: Scorching Showdown
quests.description: They may have home advantage but if you take 'em on, we'll cheer for ya! Ready!? OK! *clap* "We've got the pride! We've got the spirit! Our hunter is the best so let 'em hear it! K-A-M-U-R-A! What's that spell? KAURA! KAMURA! Goooooo Kamura!" Wooo!

quests.name: Boomy Dango
quests.description: Ah, Hunter! Hinoa asked me to make some dango stickers and, I must say, just looking at them makes my mouth water! Johoho! Complete my request, and they're yours! Now... hop to it-to it!

quests.name: The Blue Bomber's Best Bud
quests.description: I've got a special quest fur-om the Mega Man series for ya! There's a Zinogre in there that may be small, but I have a bone to pick with. Hunt it, and I'll give you the materials to forge Mega Man's trusty companion!

quests.name: Trouble in Paradise
quests.description: An Apex Rathalos and Rathian are hollerin' at each other over in the Shrine Ruins! They say don't get involved in a couple's fight but we better put a stop to this one before it really heats up and burns the whole place down!
quests.objective: Slay an Apex Rathalos and an Apex Rathian

quests.name: Diablos Deception
quests.description: Two Apex Diablos have been spotted in the Sandy Plains. Hinoa reports that their sizes differ substantially and they're going wild. Seeing them next to each other, it's hard to tell which one's nearby and which one's far away, so be careful!

quests.name: Gales of Ibushi Blow Again
quests.description: Worrying news indeed... Ibushi has been spotted in the Coral Palace. Fortunately, it has yet to meet up with its queen, but I have a terrible feeling... Hunter, you must leap into action at once. We cannot allow them to reunite!

quests.name: Clouds of Narwa Rumble Again
quests.description: Worrying news indeed... Narwa has been spotted in the Coral Palace. Fortunately, it has yet to meet up with its king, but I have a terrible feeling... Hunter, you must leap into action at once. We cannot allow them to reunite!

quests.name: Knight in Shattered Armor
quests.description: I've got a special quest fur-om Ghosts 'n Goblins Resurrection for ya! I need you to hunt three monsters covered in an eerie red aura. Get it done, and I'll give you the materials to forge a courageous knight's armor!

quests.name: Apex Arzuros Emergency
quests.description: Urgent notice from the Hunter's Guild: Unique Apex sighted, requesting its elimination ASAP. Monster appears to be far more dangerous than any Apex to date. Retreat if deemed too dangerous.

quests.name: Soaring Desire
quests.description: Sup! Heard you've been doin' it up out there in the field. I've been doin' my thing too, especially after ol' Hanenaga taught me about the Wirebug. I'd teach you if I didn't have to do this quest... If you take care of it for me, I'll hook you up with some sick Wirebug poses!
quests.objective: Slay a Royal Ludroth, a Pukei-Pukei and a Bishaten

quests.name: Heart of Rivalry
quests.description: Hey, squirt! An Apex Mizutsune and an Apex Zinogre are goin' at it out in the Flooded Forest. Who's gonna come out on top? Well, my zenny's on you because I'm sendin' ya out there! Take 'em down and I'll give ya some new titles! Now go get to it!
quests.objective: Slay an Apex Mizutsune and an Apex Zinogre

quests.name: Tempest in the Desert
quests.description: I... *wheeze* made it... *gasp* WOO! Listen...! *cough* There's a Kushala...Daora... on the loose... *gasp* You gotta do something *huff* about it...! I... ran through... the night... to warn you *wheeze* Now I need... a bit of a... lie-down...

quests.name: Rising Sun!?
quests.description: I've got a special quest fur-om OKAMI for ya! Collect the cargo strewn about the Shrine Ruins and I'll give you the materials to create layered armor that'll make your Palamute look like the legendary Sun Goddess!

quests.name: Gotta Hoard Fast!
quests.description: Oh no! Looks like Sonic dropped all of his rings! If you help us collect them all, I'll set you up with some materials for layed armor that will make you look just like us! And there's an extra reward if you do it really fast!

quests.name: Beast of the Shadows
quests.description: Ah, Hunter! The illustrations I was working on turned out so well that I decided to make them into a stickers! What do you think? Adorable, are they not? Complete my request, and they're yours! Now... hop to it-to it!

quests.name: Heart of a Warrior
quests.description: Hey, Squirt! We've got ourselves a little quest that'll determine who's the strongest hunter. My zenny's on you, but we'll see! All ya gotta do is go smack around a Goss Harag and Magnamalo in the Arena and these titles are yours! Think you're up to it? Well go get to it! Bwahahaha!
quests.objective: Hunt a Goss Harag and Magnamalo

quests.name: I Can't Do What Somnacan
quests.description: I am a professional dancer, and I wish to expand my repertoire with the graceful moves of a Somnacanth! YOU hunt one while I watch safely from afar and take notes. I'll teach you a gesture as a reward!

quests.name: Dancing Parasol, Snowy Breeze
quests.description: Ah, Hunter! Minoto asked me to make some Cahoot stickers and, johoho, they came out better than expected! Wouldn't you agree? Complete my request, and they're yours! Now... hop to it-to it!

quests.name: Heart of a Ninja
quests.description: Hey, Squirt! We've got ourselves another little quest in the Arena that'll test the best of the best. Complete it and you'll snag some new titles for yourself. Now these monsters think they're slick but my zenny's on you! Go get to it!

quests.name: Haste Makes Waste
quests.description: Seems like power alone isn't enough these days -- hunters want to look intelligent too. I'd take brawn over brains any day... I guess times are changing. Complete this request, and I'll give you the required materials.

quests.name: Arena Quest 01
quests.description: In the monster corner: Pukei-Pukei, the Toxic Tussler, the Lickin' Machine! He won't listen when you say "no tongues"! Who's got the guts to fight it with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Quest 02
quests.description: In the monster corner: Kulu-Ya-Ku, the Pulverizer, the Peckanizer! If this bird is the word, then the word is SMASH! Who's got the guts to fight it with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Quest 03
quests.description: In the monster corner: Rathian, the Queen o' Green, the Skyborne Slasher! Don't get the lady angry; she's poison! Who's got the guts to fight her with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Quest 04
quests.description: In the monster corner: Tzitzi-Ya-Ku, the Saurian Stunner, the Flashinator! This beastie's hot to trot and fine to shine! Who's got the guts to fight it with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Quest 05
quests.description: In the monster corner: Barroth, the Hulking Headbutt, the Skullcracker! Lose to this guy, and your name is mud! Who's got the guts to fight it with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Quest 06
quests.description: In the monster corner: Dodogama, the Behemoth of Boom, the Cruncher! What blows up, must bring you down! Who's got the guts to fight it with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Quest 07
quests.description: In the monster corner: Azure Rathalos, the Sapphire Sultan, the True Blue Terror! Bow down to the king of all wyverns! Who's got the guts to fight it with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Quest 08
quests.description: In the monster corner: A Radobaan-Uragaan tag team! The wheels are turning, and your number's up! Who's got the guts to fight 'em with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Quest 09
quests.description: In the monster corner: A Diablos-Black Diablos tag team! Ever had your ears pierced? Now try the extreme version! Who's got the guts to fight 'em with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Master Quest 01
quests.description: In the monster corner: Banbaro, the Ruler of the Reach, the Champ of Tramp! If you can't dig your own grave, he'll dig it for you! You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Master Quest 02
quests.description: In the monster corner: Nightshade Paolumu, the Sultan of Slumber, the Flightmare! Get caught in the sleeper hold, and it's lights out! You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Master Quest 03
quests.description: In the monster corner: Nargacuga, the Shadowy Slayer, the Nimble Ninja! If you can't see him, it's already too late! You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Master Quest 04
quests.description: In the monster corner: Acidic Glavenus, the Colonel of Corrosion, The Dino Dueler! There's no stoppin' once he gets to choppin'! You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Master Quest 05
quests.description: In the monster corner: An Odogaron-Ebony Odogaron tag team! The hounds are out, and you're about to get woofed! You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Master Quest 06
quests.description: In the monster corner: Zinogre, the Bug Zapper, the Thunder Clapper! When this pup gets to howlin', better throw the towel in! You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Arena Master Quest 07
quests.description: In the monster corner: A Tigrex-Brute Tigrex tag team! Don't get between these two, unless you wanna be a wishbone! You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: The Food Chain Dominator
quests.description: The Deviljho is a frightening presence that takes the idea of the food chain and crushes it between massive jaws! Now it's here in the New World. It's time to get investigating!

quests.name: The Blazing Sun
quests.description: A team has spotted Teostra in the Wildspire Waste. I say it's an opportune time to go and have an audience with the infernal emperor, wouldn't you say?

quests.name: Pandora's Arena
quests.description: There's a saying about a cornered animal that slips me mind— Either way, there's wounded Teostra corralled in the Special Arena. Something's up with it. Go and check it out, eh?

quests.name: No Remorse, No Surrender
quests.description: I never thought I'd live to see both the emperor and his empress in one spot. It's only fitting that you have the honor of ending their reign.

quests.name: A Visitor from Another World
quests.description: My weirdo partner won't shut up about some non-animal animal he found in the Wildspire Waste. Do you wanna tag along? Whatever it is, it's bound to be something interesting!

quests.name: The Legendary Beast
quests.description: Some kind of beast has arrived in the New World due to the instability of the aether. We have to do something otherwise every living thing in the New World is in serious danger!

quests.name: Contract: Trouble in the Ancient Forest
quests.description: Attention field team! An anomaly has been discovered in the Ancient Forest. Help the witcher resolve this issue. In this quest, you will get to play as Geralt of Rivia.

quests.name: He Taketh It with His Eyes
quests.description: It was a Behemoth, an Eorzean beast, in the Elder's Recess. Heed the moogle's advice, call upon other trustworthy hunte— adventurers to help quell this terror!

quests.name: Sterling Pride
quests.description: You hear the rumors of ol' Shattered Horn? Sounds like it's shown up in the Hoarfrost Reach, but why it's there and why its horn is broken is as clear as mud! Sounds like a mystery worth investigating, eh?

quests.name: Reveal Thyself, Destroyer
quests.description: We've traced whatever broke the Kirin's horn to the Guiding Lands. You can bet your bottom zenny that it's one tough customer, so don't let your guard down. And don't be late!

quests.name: Across the Lost Path
quests.description: We've discovered a new path in the Guiding Lands that even monsters tread carefully around. This may not be an issue from a long-term perspective, but it warrants an investigation.

quests.name: ...And My Rage for All
quests.description: A Raging Brachydios has been spotted in the Guiding Lands. Not many hunters have faced one and come back in one piece. Think you can join their ranks?

quests.name: The Fury Remains
quests.description: A Furious Rajang has been spotted in the Hoarfrost Reach. Not many hunters have faced one and come back in one piece. Think you can join their ranks?

quests.name: Dawn's Triumph
quests.description: The burning Alatreon has once again been spotted. To make matters worse, news has spread of cataclysmic natural disasters occurring in the Old World. The timing of these events is curious to say the least. They merit further investigation but Alatreon comes first.

quests.name: Blazing Black Twilight
quests.description: Not much is known of Alatreon, other than the destruction it's capable of threatens all of humanity. But this is a chance for the Commission to write history, no?

quests.name: The Black Dragon
