quests.description: We can't lavish any more praise on a hunter such as yourself, who has survived the dangers of the New World. But we do have a quest that will challenge even you, our Sapphire Star!

quests.name: Today's Special: Hunter Flambé
quests.description: Partner, we're part of the food chain too if you think about it. And that's bad news for us if a Deviljho gets a hankering for a hunter burger! So, let's hunt it down before we're lunch!

quests.name: Gale & Fangs Slay Event 3
quests.description: To the hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at your disposal, we salute you with a quest that will show us why they call you the true Sapphire Star!

quests.name: Gale & Fangs Slay Event 2
quests.description: To the hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at your disposal, we salute you with a quest that will show us why they call you the true Sapphire Star!

quests.name: Gale & Fangs Slay Event 1
quests.description: To the hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at your disposal, we salute you with a quest that will show us why they call you the true Sapphire Star!

quests.name: Empress in Full Bloom III
quests.description: They say there's a monster as pink as the cherry blossoms around these parts, is that true!? Let's see who's the strongest, you, me, or that monster! Winner gets a prize!

quests.name: Empress in Full Bloom II
quests.description: They say there's a monster as pink as the cherry blossoms around these parts, is that true!? Let's see who's the strongest, you, me, or that monster! Winner gets a prize!

quests.name: Empress in Full Bloom I
quests.description: They say there's a monster as pink as the cherry blossoms around these parts, is that true!? Let's see who's the strongest, you, me, or that monster! Winner gets a prize!

quests.name: Challenge Quest 2: Intermediate
quests.description: In the monster corner: A double dose of Odogaron! Any hunter brave enough to step into their penitentiary should prepare for the most brutal of sentences!

quests.name: Challenge Quest 1: Intermediate
quests.description: In the monster corner: A Rathalos and Tzitzi-Ya-Ku tag team! Fighting a war on two fronts is never fun, but maybe one of the monsters can *ahem* shed some light on a viable strategy!

quests.name: Kings Know No Fear
quests.description: Just looking at a Rathalos reminds me of how irrelevant I am compared to the King of the Skies. And I hate it! Help me be famous too! (Increased chance of rare material rewards, special ticket available)

quests.name: A Royal Pain
quests.description: I wouldn't mind going home, but I hate all the royal hubbub that goes with it. Fiver, remind me why I joined the Fifth. (Special ticket and increased rare material rewards)

quests.name: USJ Blazing Azure Stars!
quests.description: USJ is pleased to present the most EXPLOSIVE show ever! Our twin blue stars will show you a dance like you've never seen before! Complete our challenge, and earn some fantastic armor!

quests.name: The Blazing Sun
quests.description: A team has spotted Teostra in the Wildspire Waste. I say it's an opportune time to go and have an audience with the infernal emperor, wouldn't you say?

quests.name: Nergigante Slay Event 1
quests.description: To the hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at your disposal, we salute you with a quest that will show us why they call you the true Sapphire Star!

quests.name: Code: Red
quests.description: Legends say in a far off land, a demon hunter in a red coat offed demons with a sickeningly sweet style. How about we make a legend out of you too? If you're interested, jump in.

quests.name: The Hunter and The Blue Empress
quests.description: Only a hunter like you, who has survived the dangers of the New World, can stand tall until the end and show everyone who has the fieriest of hearts!

quests.name: The Best of the Best
quests.description: We can't lavish any more praise on a hunter such as yourself, who has survived the dangers of the New World. But we do have a quest that will challenge even you, our Sapphire Star!

quests.name: Nergigante Slay Event 4
quests.description: To the hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at your disposal, we salute you with a quest that will show us why they call you the true Sapphire Star!

quests.name: Nergigante Slay Event 3
quests.description: To the hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at your disposal, we salute you with a quest that will show us why they call you the true Sapphire Star!

quests.name: Nergigante Slay Event 2
quests.description: To the hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at your disposal, we salute you with a quest that will show us why they call you the true Sapphire Star!

quests.name: The Awakened Satsui No Hado III
quests.description: Hah, you've come to fight a real boss of a dragon, eh? Don't worry, I won't say a word about this. You just go and stop that thing with all you've got!

quests.name: The Awakened Satsui No Hado II
quests.description: Hah, you've come to fight a real boss of a dragon, eh? Don't worry, I won't say a word about this. You just go and stop that thing with all you've got!

quests.name: The Awakened Satsui No Hado I
quests.description: Hah, you've come to fight a real boss of a dragon, eh? Don't worry, I won't say a word about this. You just go and stop that thing with all you've got!

quests.name: Blue Prominence
quests.description: I was out studying the feeding habits of some seriously cute local fauna when—WOWZERS—a gigantic blue elder dragon appears! Take care of it so I can get back to research that matters!

quests.name: Infernal Monarchy
quests.description: I don't know how it happened, but we have the chance to observe Teostra and Lunastra behavior in the Wildspire Waste! This is something we can't miss! Go see for yourself, but don't get hurt!

quests.name: No Remorse, No Surrender
quests.description: I never thought I'd live to see both the emperor and his empress in one spot. It's only fitting that you have the honor of ending their reign.

quests.name: SDF: Silent, Deadly, and Fierce
quests.description: Had an interestin' fella in a white robe board me ship, looking for passage to the New World. Gave me quite a unique gift as a fee. I bet you can craft something real nice with it. If you can take care of this quest for me, it's all yours!

quests.name: Banquet in the Earthen Hall
quests.description: The mother goddess has appeared again, but now that we have the Fifth here, we can finally complete the investigation that we started decades ago! We're counting on you kids!

quests.name: Undying Alpenglow
quests.description: My home was in the path of Zorah Magdaros, and the result was tragic. Now I'm with the Fifth, and I need your help to make sure our operation is a success! I must avenge my hometown!

quests.name: A Visitor from Eorzea (Extreme)
quests.description: Another Behemoth has appeared in the Elder's Recess and is even more dangerous than the last! Summon other adventurers and quell the beast! (Extremely difficult! Rewards: Drachen layered armor and guild card title)

quests.name: The Thronetaker
quests.client: That's the New World for You!
quests.description: I finally got permission from Botanical Research to go out in the field. My partners and I stumbled upon a Teostra, Lunastra AND Nergigante! My luck freakin' sucks! I need a nap...

quests.name: No Tomorrow for Usurpers
quests.description: Our guys spotted that big, ugly flying nuisance in the Elder's Recess! Get your gear, we need you out here ASAP! (Bonus HR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: A Nose for an Eye
quests.description: In my day, we didn't need these Scoutflies to track down monsters, but this is the New World... I've located some interesting monsters for you. Go get them. (Bonus HR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Snow & Cherry Blossoms
quests.description: Hey, I came across a couple of truly terrifying monsters in the Coral Highlands. Thought you might be interested! (Bonus HR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Tracking the Delivery
quests.description: While gathering samples out in the field, I noticed a number of rare tracks. I'll need a capable hunter to get the remainder of my samples, plus gather these tracks!

quests.name: A Simple Task
quests.description: While gathering samples out in the field, I noticed a number of rare tracks. I need a capable hunter to investigate these tracks, plus gather the rest of my samples!

quests.name: Challenge Quest 2: Expert
quests.description: In the monster corner: Nergigante, the Divebombing Demon, the Prickly Punisher, the Barbed Brawler. It's half past time for the Eater of Elder's next meal, and you're on the menu!

quests.name: Challenge Quest 1: Expert
quests.description: In the monster corner: A Bazelgeuse-Uragaan tag team! You're walking into a literal minefield with these two around! Watch your step and you won't get blown up!

quests.name: Keeper of the Otherworld
quests.description: During my research, I came across a river. Just as I was about to swim across, I spotted some kind of supernatural light. Its existence defied all explanation. Help me unravel this mystery.

quests.name: Like a Moth to the Flame
quests.description: Once more, I want to see that source of energy. The one born of light that has beckoned us all here to the New World. Let us embark on this journey once again if you are ready.

quests.name: Relish the Moment
quests.description: We've discovered an insanely fierce Deviljho! It seems the cause of his bad mood is his diet of Streamstones. Quell the beast, and take those Streamstones for yourself!

quests.name: The Fury of El Dorado
quests.description: The old girl is back and stronger than ever, this time dressed to the nines in a glittering white gold coat! With the First and Fifth working together, we won't let this golden opportunity go to waste!

quests.name: When Blue Dust Surpasses Red Lust
quests.description: What is TRUE love? *sigh* One must witness the passionate bond between the empress and emperor of flame to truly know. Get too close and surely you'll get burned. Like I did...

quests.name: The Heralds of Destruction Cry
quests.description: I still remember when that thing showed up. I heard horns blaring in my head. It sounded like a song of destruction. I need help with my research, so those horns can stop!

quests.name: The Eye of the Storm
quests.description: Kushala's existence reminds us of how great and fearful nature is. But it also reminds us of those who stood up against the beast. Stand tall hunter, and return the skies to blue.

quests.name: The Scorn of the Sun
quests.description: When I first fought a Teostra back in the Old World, my fear washed over me, but it gave me the fire to fight. But now I realized it's calmness, not fear, that you need to slay it.

quests.name: A Whisper of White Mane
quests.description: At first I thought it was an illusion, staring down at me. That white mist gave me chills I'll never forget. I need your help to confirm my findings.

quests.name: The Deathly Quiet Curtain
quests.description: The truly horrifying things are the ones sleeping in silence, no? But what could it be? The Third Fleet urges you to press on, to lift the curtain off of this mystery and feed our obsession.

quests.name: The Name's Lavasioth!
quests.description: Yo, we got asked to research a monster that no one ever wants to research! You know the one, that big floppy fishy that likes to lounge around in the lava! Yeah, THAT one! (Special ticket rewards)

quests.name: The Greatest Jagras
quests.description: So I heard that a hunter had a Great Jagras cornered, but when they went to finish it off, a shadow appeared. What do you think it is? Heh, go out and find out for yourself! (Special ticket rewards)

quests.name: A Visitor from Eorzea
quests.description: A Behemoth has appeared in the Elder's Recess. Conventional methods won't work, call upon other trustworthy hunte— adventurers to help quell the beast!

quests.name: Contract: Woodland Spirit
quests.description: A portal appeared in the Ancient Forest, and a strange creature came through it. The beast is called a woodland spirit and it's extremely dangerous. Quest level close to Death March! difficulty in The Witcher 3.

quests.name: Pearl Snatchers
quests.description: Ooooh! My best assistant came to lend me a hand! Think you can catch me some of those fluffy duffy Pearlspring Macaques? For what? Duh! To play with—er, I mean to research of course, you silly hunter! (Special material rewards upon completion.)

quests.name: Duffel Duty
quests.description: You ready to lend me a hand? Oh, goodie! I need you to capture some Duffel Penguins for me. You gotta be quick, though. They'll give you the flipper then you give you the slip! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Flora Frostbite
quests.client: Greetings, it's me again! Ha ha!
quests.description: The Reach is so cold your ears will fall off, or so I heard. Earmuffs would do the trick, or maybe some—!? I got it! Yes, INSPIRATION! To the message boards! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Skyward Snipers
quests.description: You've seen those big Grandfather Mantagrells being all floaty in the air, right? My notes say they're especially weak to sudden shocks. I bet if you use your slinger you can get one for me to play with—I mean study, of course! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: A Fish to Whet Your Appetite
quests.description: Not only are those big boys sharp to a fault, if you can haul them here fresh as a daisy, they might be useful as a weapon too! So get on out there and snag some, will ya? (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Trophy Fishin'
quests.description: Don't think you can eat 'em and I know gramps would be reel upset if I plopped one down in front of him for supper. But sounds like mighty good fun tangoin' with two tundra trouts! (Increased HR/MR points and special material rewards upon completion.)

quests.name: The Lord of the Underworld Beckons
quests.description: Those things—like felvine, I tell ya! I just can't get enough! If you can go meow-t and get your paws on some more, I'd really a-purr-eciate it! I'll even reward you with lots of bone materials fur your troubles! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: A Bunch of Sticks in the Mud
quests.description: Some roaming Banbaro have adapted to the Wildspire and are using mounds of mud to attack hunters! Careful out there, everyone! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Desert Desserts
quests.description: Ah, Hunter! I've caught wind of a delicacy called a Hardfruit, which makes for a delightful snack. It's a bit of a trek, but bring some back for me and I'll reward you with lots of ore! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: The New World
quests.description: Looks like I'm back in this world again, but where are those two? Guess I better look for them... In this quest, you will get to play as Artemis.

quests.name: To Our World
quests.description: Why is that thing still alive? I thought we killed it! Does that mean I'm in the...? At any rate, I need to find a way back to my world. In this quest, you will get to play as Artemis.

quests.name: Fetching Light Pearls
quests.description: I saw those Kelbi eyes glow like a pearl in the dark! Then it struck me. Yes, INSPIRATION! To the message boards! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Every Hunter's Dream II
quests.description: A hunter came by with blueprints for Palico equipment they wanted me to craft. I still have the prints lying around, so if you want one of your own, get me the materials and I'll start workin'. (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Paolumu Lullabies
quests.description: The Admiral and Chef managed to capture a Nightshade Paolumu, but something seemed pawfully off. I didn't mention anything to those two, but purrhaps you could take a look, Meowster?

quests.name: Challenge Quest 1: MR Intermediate
quests.description: In the monster corner: A Tobi-Kadachi-Viper Tobi-Kadachi tag team! Stay on your toes against this tandem because the fur is about to fly! You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Balloon Fight
quests.description: OK. I, uh, admit that I went a little crazy with the party prep, but I swear I did NOT blow up those balloons. Pop those pests and the Second Fleet Master will hook you up with armor spheres!

quests.name: A New Troublemaker in Town
quests.description: —and you know what would be fascinating? Hunting an Anjanath AND a Banbaro at the same time! I would certainly dole out more HR/MR points to any hunter who'd take up that challenge! Yes, can you imagine it, Hunter? Going at it with those two brutes—

quests.name: Colorful Carnival
quests.description: Yeah, time to get it done! I got an assignment from the scholars to pick up a couple of whatcha-ma-call-sacs. I'm gonna do it all in one go! (Increased HR/MR points upon completion.)

quests.name: Hunter-Blunderer
quests.description: We were supposed to go out to get some stuff for Analytics, but my partner goofed and went on a different quest! Can you take care of this while I fetch him? Geez...this bozo. (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Camoflawed
quests.description: The young miss I work with needs to research some critter in a Rath nest and almost went wearin' an herbivore disguise. Good thing I stopped her before she got swooped up. Could you go hunt that Rathian so she can get her critter fix? (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Kadachi Twins
quests.description: It's so freakin' cold out here that I came up with a design for some warm armor based on a monster! It looks strong, yes, strong indeed! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Every Hunter's Dream III
quests.description: A hunter came by with a blueprint of a weapon they wanted. I still have the prints lying around, so if you want one of your own, get me the materials and I'll start workin'. (Special material rewards)

quests.name: 50 Shades of White
quests.description: To all hunters who yearn for action in the Arena, this quest is for you! Go head to head with our combatants, and earn special materials to craft weapons! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: The True Tyrant
quests.description: We salute all hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at their disposal. Embark on this quest that will challenge you and may the Sapphire Star light your way!

quests.name: A Sky & Sea of Fire
quests.description: They're everywhere! I can hear the treacherous wings of fire above me, and I can feel the smoldering glare coming from that lava! Help! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: A Curious Experiment
quests.description: Hey, what do you think would happen if a Diablos charged at an inflated Paolumu? I've been thinking about this for way too long and now I can't sleep. Do you think you can find out for me? (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Soaked and Shivering
quests.description: I was SO looking forward to going out on a hunt in a place that's not cold, but it IS cold. FREEZING COLD! And it's wet too! That's it! I am SO done. I'm going home... (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Fired-Up Bruisers
quests.description: —to hunt a Glavenus AND an Uragaan simultaneously, yes! That's the stuff dreams are made of! I'd most certainly dole out extra HR/MR points upon completion to the hunters who—

quests.name: When the Swift Meets the Roar
quests.description: Expect things to get hot and tense in this quest! But don't worry, you'll get your fill of decorations if you come out of this in one piece! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Seeing is Believing
quests.description: Yo, Scrawny. This hungover hunter came by sayin' he's seein' things in the Arena. He was so shook up about it that it's made him quit drinkin'. Go check it out for him, will ya? (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Beef is Never a Mi-steak
quests.client: Been a while! How you doing!?
quests.description: No matter how much I chow down, I'm never full. Guess I'm still a growing boy! I need my protein, or maybe—!? I got it! Yes, INSPIRATION! To the message boards! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Challenge Quest 2: MR Intermediate
quests.description: In the monster corner: An Anjanath-Fulgur Anjanath tag...team...? Bless their hearts, I think their lil' ol' arms are too short to tag... You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: The Desert Dash
quests.description: Scouts have spotted a couple of highly dangerous monsters speeding across the Wildspire. Head to the locale and take care of both threats! And don't be late! (Increased HR/MR points upon completion)

quests.name: In the Depths of the Forest
quests.description: They say that Anjanaths are built for the forest. They roam it like kings, but now that an Azure Rathalos has showed up, we got a real fight on our hands! (Increased HR/MR points upon completion.)

quests.name: Servants of the Vale
quests.description: Two monsters have staked claim to the Rotten Vale, Hunter. But no matter who wins, the Commission loses. We need someone like you to get in there and drive both of them out! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Scores of Ores
quests.description: Dang, mining is a workout! If I had a cooler pickaxe maybe this wou—...!? I got it! Yes, INSPIRATION! To the message boards! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: The Winter Blues
quests.description: This cold reminds me of the Hinterlands, but it drips with an eerie, tranquil smell. This must be looked into, yes? Run along now... (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: The Assassin
quests.description: I dreamt of a man with the grace of an assassin...and ever since, I've been going bonkers thinking about what I want to work on next. Ya gotta help me out here! (Upgrades the Assassin's Hood upon first completion.)

quests.name: USJ: Shine On Forever
quests.description: Special delivery from USJ to you: the perfect stage for you to sparkle with a monster that truly shines! May the shine never end! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: RE: Return of the Bioweapon
quests.description: We've discovered a strange condition which is horrifyingly unaffected by effluvial resistance! If it's not effluvial buildup, then what is it? Help us, Hunter, and you'll be generously compensated! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Old Dog, New Trick
quests.description: What a proud figure I must make, sitting here with my arms crossed. But perhaps I should learn the ways of the new generation, starting with the clutch claw? I heard a Gold Melding Ticket would be the prize, heh.

quests.name: Talk About a Party Foul...
quests.description: Wooo, that was one GNARLY party! But some, uh, party pooper left all his party poop all over the place... Sorry, Player. Someone's gotta clean up this mess and it ain't me! But if you do, the Second Fleet Master will hook you up with some sweet armor spheres!

quests.name: A Reason Behind The Hunger
quests.description: Perhaps the reason why this type of Deviljho is constantly hunting is that it's lost its ability to feel full? Perhaps I can empathize with its plight. I too, crave... My hunger for knowledge is insatiable! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: We Three Kings
quests.description: Thunder. Wind. Fire. Nature's wonders in their purest form. So, we fight purity with purity. Pick your weapon, hunter. And fight. (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: A Chilling Entrance
quests.description: It's cold today, better get a scarf to warm up. I wonder what'll happen if I wrap my hea—...!? I got it! INSPIRATION! To the message boards! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Talk About a Party Foul...
quests.description: Wooo, that was one GNARLY party! But some, uh, party pooper left all his party poop all over the place... Sorry, Player. Someone's gotta clean up this mess and it ain't me! But if you do, the Second Fleet Master will hook you up with some sweet armor spheres!

quests.name: Farewell to the Frozen
quests.description: To the hunters who have survived the dangers of the New World, I hope you can display your full potential one more time. Show them that the Sapphire Star can never be frozen!

quests.name: The Conqueror of Hoarfrost
quests.description: We salute all hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at their disposal. Embark on this quest that will challenge you and may the Sapphire Star light your way!

quests.name: Aiming for the Light
quests.description: We salute all hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at their disposal. Embark on this quest that will challenge you and may the Sapphire Star light your way!

quests.name: A Star That Will Never Dim
quests.description: We salute all hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at their disposal. Embark on this quest that will challenge you and may the Sapphire Star light your way!

quests.name: Wearer of the Iceborne Crown
quests.description: We salute all hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at their disposal. Embark on this quest that will challenge you and may the Sapphire Star light your way!

quests.name: USJ: Ballet of Frost
quests.description: Special delivery from USJ to you: the perfect stage for you to duel with a monster with fangs of frost! May the excitement never end! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Dawn of the Death Star
quests.description: Alatreon has been sighted in the Secluded Valley. It screams, like an icy dead star that rejects the light. But it's time for the Commission to let the world know of this blazing black abomination!

quests.name: Alt Rock Recess
quests.description: The monsters in the Elder's Recess are used to hanging tough, but today they're especially irritated. This could be a huge boon to our research, so suit up and head out!

quests.name: Ballad of the Hoarfrost
quests.description: The monsters of the Reach tend to keep to themselves, but today they're at each other's throats! This could be a huge boon to our research, so suit up and head out!

quests.name: Wolf Out of Hell
quests.description: My apologies. I spent years researching monsters, giving everything to the Commission. But I lost everything to THIS one. I need you to step in, for I fear I won't be able to keep my cool. (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: The Eternal Gold Rush
quests.description: The mother goddess has reappeared. This time, our objective is to slay her. Get the quest from your handler or the quest board. Stand tall against her fury and return safely!

quests.name: The Wrath of Thunder Descends
quests.description: They say lightning never strikes the same place twice, but I wouldn't take my chances here! Get through this in one piece and you'll get your fill of decorations! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Ode to the Destruction
quests.description: Scouts have sighted an unusually fierce Ruiner Nergigante out in the field. We need you to investigate. Expect some Great Spiritvein Gems as a reward for your trouble. (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: In the Tempest's Wake
quests.description: When I was a young girl, a Kushala Daora passed by our village. We hid in our homes, afraid of what tragedy it might leave in its wake. And now it's here... May this Sealed Feystone be incentive enough for you to put a stop to this tempest.

quests.name: Day of Ruin
quests.description: A blazing sun in a sunless land—I guess every life burns as brightly as it can, no matter where it finds itself. Just like we did those forty years ago... Anyway, I've prepared a Sealed Feystone for after you've laid this sun to rest.

quests.name: The Cold Never Bothered Me
quests.description: We've driven the "Blue Flame" into the cold prison of the supply cache, but now it seems to burn brighter than ever in its defiance. Extinguish it before it burns us all, and I'll reward your efforts with a Sealed Feystone.

quests.name: The Evening Star
quests.description: Alatreon has been sighted in the Secluded Valley. It seethes, like a burning star that revels in the darkness. But it's time for the Commission to let the world know of this blazing black abomination!

quests.name: Fade to Black
quests.description: We've been tasked with slaying Fatalis, a monster known only in legends handed-down. This beast will test all of your limits, but I know you'll be ready.

quests.name: Symphony of the Coral
quests.description: The Coral Highlands is relatively peaceful, so it's not every day we see this many monsters duking it out. This could be a huge boon to our research, so suit up and head out!

quests.name: The Last White Knight
quests.description: We've finally found it! The tree top assassin that controls the frost. "The Last White Knight", they call it. Outmuscling it is out of the question. No, only the most devoted can topple this beast. I await your report, Hunter.

quests.name: The Distant Dark Tide
quests.description: My mother used to lead a hunting party and told me once of a story where pleasant weather turned to violent storms, forcing the party back and spoiling a fine expedition. Perhaps the cause was Namielle. I hope your hunt divulges some answers...

quests.name: The Place Where Winter Sleeps
quests.description: As leader of this hunt, I've been granted authority to add new recruits to our ranks. Our target is an incredibly ferocious Velkhana. Want a challenge? Then help us send it to its end!

quests.name: Don't Forget The Earplugs!
quests.description: An awfully big Shepherd Hare is inside the arena. Looks a bit different from the usual variety, but no mistaking it's a Shepherd Hare with those ears! You wanna take a look and get some INSPIRATION too!? (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Monkey Business
quests.description: I just spotted a gigantic Goldspring Macaque! No, seriously! The way it roars into the sky and that electric golden fur, there's no mistaking it! It's going to be my source of INSPIRATION! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: The Naked Truth
quests.description: I've suddenly reached enlightenment. I now know the truth! All life cannot attain their true potential unless they take the same form as when they came into this world. And that means...INSPIRATION! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Mew are Number One!
quests.description: Meow, child, we all know that you are the Commission's number one hunter. The only thing you're missing is a golden trophy, so I've gone and fixed up a quest for you to go out and get one. I even threw in a few goodies too. Be back in time fur dinner, meow!

quests.name: Tears from Nirvana
quests.description: When people travel to the other side, there are places full of fear and sadness that you must bear alone. You'll know that same feeling if you face a Blackveil Vaal Hazak. (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Mighty Muscle Monkey Madness
quests.description: Yeah, hunters are something else. "This won't do... I'm not satisfied", they said with a fire in their eye. Their passion for muscles easily surpasses my inspiration! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: A Farewell to Zinogre
quests.description: The most hunted monster ever, how wonderful! Let me throw you hunters a curveball and offer a slightly different Zinogre! Those shiny things on the ground may look tempting, but be careful not to get a paw to the face!

quests.name: Rotten Canzone
quests.description: The monsters in the Rotten Vale are usually combative, but today they're especially irritated. This could be a huge boon to our research, so suit up and head out!

quests.name: Heavy Metal in the Waste
quests.description: The Wildspire is a vast stretch of land, so it's not every day we see this many monsters duking it out. This could be a huge boon to our research, so suit up and head out!

quests.name: Sterling Pride
quests.description: You hear the rumors of ol' Shattered Horn? Sounds like it's shown up in the Hoarfrost Reach, but why it's there and why its horn is broken is as clear as mud! Sounds like a mystery worth investigating, eh?

quests.name: Muscle Monkey Madness
quests.description: Boy, I wish I could be as strong as you hunters! Maybe instead of getting buff, I could wear—!? I got it! Yes, INSPIRATION! To the message boards! (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Point of No Return
quests.description: We need you to do some recon on that red monster. Remember, don't get in over your head. Get in, find out what you need, then get out.

quests.name: The Red Dragon
quests.description: Safi'jiiva, the mature form of Xeno'jiiva... Reports confirm that it's siphoning energy from its surroundings to heal its wounds. We need to eliminate this threat before it's too late!

quests.name: Special Arena: MR Stygian Zinogre
quests.description: A new challenger: Stygian Zinogre, the Dean of Dracophage, the Mighty Mephisto! You better be hungry like the wolf if you wanna survive! Two fighters enter the Special Arena, but only one leaves!

quests.name: Achy Brachy Heart
quests.description: My senior hunting friend went off to slay a Raging Brachydios once, and when I asked about it she just said, "I just don't think you'd understand." Can you believe that? I almost blew up at her! Now I have to go see it for myself.

quests.name: All That Glitters is Furious
quests.description: We know of the Furious Rajang, but only just that. Do you know why? Because when it spots you, it's already over. Can our Sapphire Star stand up to the golden fury?

quests.name: A Shocking Climax
quests.description: I have located the ones who command the thunder. I left the task to a group of Fifth Fleet hunters, but they have yet to return. It's up to you now. (Special material rewards)

quests.name: Yodeling in the Forest
quests.description: The Ancient Forest is a living maze, so it's not every day we see this many monsters duking it out. This could be a huge boon to our research, so suit up and head out!

quests.name: Challenge Quest 1: MR Expert
quests.description: In the monster corner: Yian Garuga, the Screamin' Demon, the Beaked Berzerker! You've never seen crazy like this before! You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Challenge Quest 2: MR Expert
quests.description: In the monster corner: Deviljho, the food chain dominator, the pulverizing pickle! This is one hoss that likes to throw its weight around! You ready to duke it out with set weapons and armor?

quests.name: Fear No Scars
quests.description: We salute all hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at their disposal. Embark on this quest that will challenge you and may the Sapphire Star light your way!

quests.name: Power and Technique
quests.description: We salute all hunters who have conquered the New World using everything at their disposal. Embark on this quest that will challenge you and may the Sapphire Star light your way!

quests.name: Moonlit Howl
quests.description: I saw a Zinogre in the Coral Highlands! This is it—the perfect opportunity for a study case on Fulgurbugs in the New World! I won't rest until I—until YOU get me some specimens! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: I Am Tranquil, I Am Sound
quests.description: My purr-ank-loving furr-iend told me about this meownster that's the definition of "calm"! I gotta see it for myself! Maybe I should take some earplugs...? Nah, I'll be fine! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: A Roar that Splinters the Sky
quests.client: I thought my ears would bleed!
quests.description: As soon as we heard that roar in the distance, the hunter I was with sounded the retreat. Good thing, too—had we heard that roar up close, well, I'm sure I would have been its dinner! (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: A Glance of Silver
quests.description: At first I thought it was just some light glancing off the rocks in the Elder's Recess, but it was HIM. I never thought I'd live to see this day! It makes me glad I came to the New World. (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: The Moon is a Harsh Queen
quests.description: The golden empress has been spotted. We need the Fifth to prepare and head out. Take care, or the empress may turn the tables on you before you know it. (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Razzled, Frazzled, and Dazzled
quests.description: The Admiral and some Fivers were talking some absolutely nonsense when they went off on a quest to hunt a Rajang. The Research Commission sure has a lot of hairballed hunters, huh? (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Scars Tell the Whole Story
quests.description: Us hunters have seen a lot of crazy stuff in our day, but nothing comes close to personifying crazy as that big purple chicken does! Don't lose your cool now. (Bonus HR/MR points rewarded upon completion.)

quests.name: Brand New Brute
quests.description: Whoa, no wonder this Brute Tigrex's so clean, it's the least hunted monster! Is it crying tears of joy? Wait, those tears look a lot like armor spheres...hmm. Odd. (You cannot obtain monster materials from this quest)

quests.name: Tetranadon Blockade
quests.description: As I said previously, there's a Tetranadon making a nuisance of itself in the Jungle. This mission is essential for securing safe passage between Elgado and Kamura. Now then, , the Fierce! Show me what you're made of!

quests.name: Barroth to a Great Start
quests.description: Ta-daaah! I invented this revolutionary fertilizer by mixing all sorts of stuff with a Barroth tail! I'll make a killin' if I can mass-produce this, but I ran outta tail! Can ya go hunt a Barroth for me?

quests.name: You Had Me at Poofy
quests.description: OK, picture this: Royal Ludroth stuffed animals. Eh? EH? You can totally see it, right? With their little poofy mane, they'd be a hit! And why stop there? Kitchen sponges, bath sponges!? All we need is a little..."product research."

quests.name: A Sinking Feeling
quests.description: After getting my first ship, I was tasked with ferrying knights to the Jungle, but Hermitaur and Velociprey roam the shores! I don't like the look of this... I JUST became captain! I'm not ready to go down with the ship!
quests.objective: Slay a total of 15 Hermitaur or Velociprey

quests.name: Need a Hunter, ASAP!
quests.description: es, yes. Greetings. Now if you don't mind, I didn't come all this way for formalities. I came here to research monsters. And I intend to do just that! I require that you hunt a Kulu-Ya-Ku immediately. Well... What are you waiting for?

quests.name: Buggin' Out!
quests.description: Ew! EW! Get them away from me! Gross, gross, GROSS! Like, why didn't someone tell me the Jungle would be literally CRAWLING with bugs? Monsters? OK. But, bugs? BUGS? HELLO! I did NOT sign up for this, OK? Yuck.
quests.objective: Slay a total of 20 Vespoid or Hornetaur

quests.name: Reap What You Saw
quests.description: I was having the darndest time trying to cut my grass—'bout cut my dang hand off—when I seen the darndest thing! This darn monster did one li'l twirl and mowed down just about everything around it! Maybe if I watch you hunt one, I can figure out how it does that.

quests.name: The Red Rolling Terror
quests.description: omeone! Help pleeeeeeease! I crossed paths with a Volvidon and it chased me up a tree! You gotta hurry! It keeps spittin' at me and lickin' the bottom of my boots! I'm sendin' this message via bug— sorry for the bug goo in advance!

quests.name: It Could be Worse...
quests.description: So funny story, I get barbequed by an Aknosom so I stop, drop, and roll, right? But I keep rolling and rolling...and rolling...and roll— Anyway, I'm all dizzy now and my buns are toasted. Think you can go and finish the job for me?

quests.name: [REDACTED]
quests.description: A certain VIP may or may not be set to visit the Outpost, but two Great Wroggi may or may not have appeared on the road in. We may or may not need you to hunt it.

quests.name: BRRRR Plus ZZZzzz Equals?
quests.description: Help! I was fishin' in the Frost Islands, when bam! a Lagombi was all like RAWR with a snow- ball, and I was all BRRRR, and then boom! A Great Baggi went all BAAARFFF, and I was all ZZZzzzzz...
quests.objective: Hunt a Lagombi and a Great Baggi

quests.name: The Good, the Bad, and Lagombi
quests.description: Hunter, good... Lagombi, bad... Wirebugs, good... Snowball, bad... Big ears, good... Sonic Bomb, bad... Many bombs, good... Forget bombs, bad...

quests.name: The Jungle Guidebook
quests.description: For the sake of my publication, I need you to hunt three monsters. I wish to record the nitty-gritty details of these fearsome beasts! Once complete, merchants and travelers will be able to navigate the Jungle safely!

quests.name: Supply Line Shell Game
quests.description: I came up with the pur-fect recipe to help meow-t hunters and researchers in the field, but the ingredients can only be found in Daimyo Hermitaur territory! Can you help me secure my supplies by removing those crabs from the culinary equation?

quests.name: Uninvited Guest
quests.description: So a Daimyo Hermitaur found its way into the Shrine Ruins, huh? Well, time for a little Kamura welcome. But be careful, I hear that shell of theirs is darn near impossible to penetrate. Not a problem for a smart hunter like you! Bwahaha! Now go get to it!

quests.name: Catnap Ruined
quests.description: All the shade in the Shrine Ruins makes it purr-fect fur napping, but two Arzuros are making such a ruckus with their tussling, I can't catch a wink! I need you to get back my mew-ty sleep, Hunter!

quests.name: Provoking an Anjanath's Wrath
quests.description: A Wyverian researcher has taken it upon himself to venture out in the Flooded Forest alone. It comes as no surprise that going out there by himself was a stupid idea. And now he's in danger. My apologies, but could I ask you to rescue him?

quests.name: A Dangerous Dare ♪
quests.description: Nothing wrong with peaceful days, but a guy needs excitement from time to time. Want to do a test of courage tonight at the Shrine Ruins? Oh, I won't be going, of course. Tell me how it went, and I'll give you an armor recipe!
quests.objective: Hunt a Rathian and a Bishaten

quests.name: Pinecone Pelting Panic
quests.description: I've been thinking of creating some nourishing dango for all you brave hunters. I hear that the pinecones hoarded by Blood Orange Bishaten contain a healthy sap. Could you keep the monkeys busy while I purr-ocure the pinecones? Thanks!

quests.name: Bird Wyvern Jamboree
quests.description: We've gotten word of a merchant lost deep in the Shrine Ruins. We have a bead on their location, but we've also gotten word of an Aknosom and a Kulu-Ya-Ku there. Hunt down both, and we'll rescue the merchant.
quests.objective: Hunt an Aknosom and a Kulu-Ya-Ku

quests.name: The Assault of the Scarlet Tengu
quests.description: A Blood Orange Bishaten has been frequently attacking other monsters in the Shrine Ruins. They are fiercely territorial species and if this one makes its nest here, I'm afraid it will attract more of them. Deal with the beast at once!

quests.name: A Shocking, Sloppy Synthesis
quests.description: One locks you up, one knocks you out—mud and lightning's a scary combo, ain't it! Maybe it wouldn't faze a fierce hunter, but... Heh, as if! Anyway, I got a double-header request here, right up your alley.
quests.objective: Hunt a Jyuratodus and a Tobi-Kadachi

quests.name: BZZZZZ or ZZZZzzzz Pt. 2
quests.description: Ugh! My soon to be ex-boyfriend has done lost his mind! He thinks Somnacanth are longer than Khezu. HELLO! The stretchy necks!? Duh! I've had it with him. I'm SO done... Anyway, can you go out there and give Khezzy my number? Thanks!
quests.objective: Hunt a Khezu and a Somnacanth

quests.name: Skulking Among the Sand
quests.description: Heeelp! I went hunting in the Sandy Purr-lains with my meowster, but we can't handle a single monster—much less THREE! I hate to say it, but we aren't up to scratch for this! We need a veteran to take the reins!

quests.name: In Pursuit of the Khezuit
quests.description: Have you heard of Khezuits? White fruit rarely found in arctic regions where Khezu live. It even looks like one! Wouldn't you know it, one's just about to ripen! I'll grab the fruit, you handle the Khezu.

quests.name: A Fond Fur-Well
quests.description: Soon my fur-iend's moving away across the sea and I wanna send 'em some flowers from the Jungle, but two monsters are stomping up the place! Hope there's enough left fur a bouquet...
quests.objective: Hunt a Tobi-Kadachi and a Tetranadon

quests.name: Plant Probe Pests
quests.description: I'm trying to conduct a botanical survey in the Flooded Forest, but monsters keep getting in my way, ESPECIALLY those Gajau and Ludroth. I'm sick of this! Please, I just want to finish my work! Get rid of 'em so I can do my job already!
quests.objective: Slay a total of 15 Gajau or Ludroth

quests.name: Now That's What I Call Great!
quests.description: Welcome to the Arena, folks! And boy do we have a show for you tonight! The Greatest of the Greats are all here and it's about to GO DOWN! These monsters are ready to fight tooth and nail for the title! Let's rumble!

quests.name: Shrine Ruined
quests.description: I went to the Shrine Ruins to take in the ancient architecture, but these two beasties started goin' at it! A fight between those two would bring down all the old buildings. Go tell 'em to take it somewhere else!
quests.objective: Hunt a Great Izuchi and a Rathian

quests.name: Messed Up Situation
quests.description: This is a nightmare... This Jyuratodus jumped out of the sludge and attacked me and now my stuff's all caked in mud! This is my best suit, too! I'm gonna go take a bath, can you take that punk to the cleaners?

quests.name: Pent-Up Frustrations
quests.description: commute through the Sandy Plains to trade at the Outpost, but when night falls, there's this weird rock wall blocking my route. What gives? Now I have to take the long way around... Argh! Somebody do something!

quests.name: Rumble in the Jungle
quests.description: I've been hearing this sound from the Jungle lately—a kind of electric buzzing? I admit I'm curious, but I get shivers thinking about what awaits at the source. Think you could take a look, Hunter?

quests.name: Poison Drops in the Sand
quests.description: Wowzers! A Pukei-Pukei in the Sandy Plains! They're cute an' all with their googly eyes and colorful feathers, but what's NOT cute is all that poison they drip everywhere! It gets all over everything! Even other critters!

quests.name: Somnacanth Sleep Aid
quests.description: *yawn* I'm a sleeping fiend, so I wanna make a pillow that's up to the nappy task. Getting *yawn* knocked out by a Somnacanth's like a gift from the sandman himself. If you hunt one for me, it'd really *yawn* help my snooze cruise.

quests.name: The Alabaster Devourer
quests.description: Feet trudge through falling snow. Naught but my footsteps, no sound, alone? I turn my gaze to the crunchy crunch—wet, gaping maw, to make me its lunch! I run, run, to no avail. Someone, uh, out...me...bail?

quests.name: The Queen's Garden
quests.description: I aspire to charming conduct becoming of a lovely lady. That's why I want to observe the graciousness of the queen inhabiting the Jungle. I'll observe from the flowers. You'll protect me, won't you?

quests.name: Sour Grapes
quests.description: I've been searching for fruit in the Jungle, but keep coming up short. Blue fur and tail marks tells me this is the work of a Bishaten. This can't go on forever, so I need you to hunt me into a better harvest!

quests.name: Keep it Busy
quests.description: Ugh! As if I didn't have enough paperwork as it is, and now I have to write down what I just got finished talking to you about... Talk about inefficient! Anyway, you know the deal: You hunt the monster, I procure the Qurio!

quests.name: The Mother of All Medicines!?
quests.description: I've learned my trade by walking hill and dale gathering ingredients for decades. Mix Tobi-Kadachi needles, Rathian spikes, and Hermitaur shell together to stop bug bite itches! Ouch, they got me again!

quests.name: Tempering the Fierce
quests.description: Well, well, well, Squirt! Tales of your deeds have made it all the way back to Kamura! We're all proud of ya, so we gotcha a li'l something. But we ain't givin' it to ya, until we test your mettle! Sound good? Now go get to it!

quests.name: Studying Starvation Effects
quests.description: Does hunger lower the abilities of all organisms? I need you to look into this! Hunt the two gluttons: Anjanath and Pukei-Pukei, and tell me how they stack up, you know, compared to usual. Got something for ya when you get back!
quests.objective: Hunt an Anjanath and a Pukei-Pukei

quests.name: Desert Lost and Found
quests.description: My li'l bro suddenly spouted off about heading to the Sandy Plains. When I dragged the reason out of him, he said his buddy lost his "treasure" there. What's a bro to do? I'll comb the sand, you watch my back.

quests.name: Troublemaker Trio
quests.description: Could be my imagination, but the monsters of the Flooded Forest look spooked these days. I asked around, and a trio of troublemaking monsters seem to be the culprits. Think you can go check it out?

quests.name: Stitching a Wintry Wardrobe
quests.description: Lovely cloth, splendid thread, a sturdy needle—all I need to sew a dress! Now it's just a matter of design. I'd love to see an Aurora Somnacanth amid the icy tundra. Could you escort me to the Frost Islands?
quests.objective: Hunt an Aurora Somnacanth and a Magnamalo

quests.name: Shady Activity
quests.description: Hey, you! Yes, YOU! I heard you're going after the two Nargacuga in the Flooded Forest! As a dyed-in- the-thickfur Nargacuga fan, I can't let you! What's that? I can use their materials to make cute Narga-goods? Well, OK. JUST THIS ONCE!

quests.name: Garangolm Gone Mad
quests.description: We've received an urgent message that a Garangolm is going berserk. If we don't do something soon, I'm afraid someone might get seriously injured or worse! Well, Hunter, can we leave this one to you?

quests.name: Freedom from a Frigid Future!
quests.description: Aaaaah! Arctic monsters are inching ever closer to our village! At this rate, we'll be covered in ice until we can't even sleep at night! Just thinking about it gives me chills! You've gotta stop them!

quests.name: In His Master's Footsteps
quests.description: Someday I wanna be just like my master so I train every day in the Shrine Ruins. Well, I used to train every day, until all those monsters showed up. Can you get rid of 'em so I can get back to training?

quests.name: The Hot and Cold Treatment
quests.description: Hasn't the tem-purr-ature in the Citadel been all over the place lately? Ice chunks and flaming pinecones flying all over... My cargo's done fur at this rate. Do something about the purr-rojectiles at least!
quests.objective: Hunt a Goss Harag and a Blood Orange Bishaten

quests.name: Soft or Spotty?
quests.description: I'm trying to come up with the design for a new dress, and I want to base it on a monster! The fluffy Gowngoat, or the cute li'l spotted Boggi, which should I choose!? I can't decide! Go and check them out, please!
quests.objective: Slay a total of 15 Gowngoats or Boggi

quests.name: A Keen-Eyed Observation
quests.description: Salutations, Hunter. I would ask your assistance in a Fanged Wyvern survey. There are many survey candidates, but this time we seek a Tobi-Kadachi and a Magnamalo. We appreciate your cooperation.
quests.objective: Hunt a Tobi-Kadachi and a Magnamalo

quests.name: Rock, Razor, Pincers
quests.description: Come one, come all! Today's catch is sure to get your mouth waterin'! But don't whip your garlic butter out just yet! These two crabs are boilin' mad! It's out of the frying pan, into the fire with these two! If you can handle the heat, dinner's served!
quests.objective: Hunt a Daimyo Hermitaur and a Shogun Ceanataur

quests.name: A Tale of Two Titans
quests.description: I felt it that day! The tale of a Garangolm and a Somnacanth— of a great man in love with a songstress! Still, peace isn't enough to show their love! I'll watch from the shadows, you get their hearts pumping!
quests.objective: Hunt a Garangolm and a Somnacanth

quests.name: Purging Hatred
quests.description: *channeling* There exists a creature burning with hatred that stalks the frozen hell searching for souls to consume. For its sins, it must be... "purified." I will prepare the ritual to cleanse its spirit, you release the beast from its mortal coil!

quests.name: A Sandy Spider Nest
quests.description: My sister went to the Sandy Plains on an investigation, but only her Cohoot came back, delivering an awful message: Rakna-Kadaki have her pinned down there. If anything happens to her, I... I... Please, Hunter! You must help!

quests.name: Shadow in the Jungle
quests.description: I am taught to be one with the shadows but never have I seen a shadow move through the Jungle at such tremendous speed. What could it have been? An assassin from a rival clan? A spirit? Nevertheless, such a threat cannot be allowed to exist. Eliminate it.

quests.name: Nocturnal Nuisances
quests.description: We've been getting more and more reports of Anjanath and Tobi-Kadachi assaults in the Jungle as of late. Guarding the night roads is our job, but their ferocity is overwhelming and many a guard has been injured. Could you do something about them?
quests.objective: Hunt an Anjanath and a Tobi-Kadachi

quests.name: Oh, My Garsh Harag
quests.description: My son loves playin' outside, and Jeez Louise, it's gettin' pretty cold out there. If I don't make him some warm clothes he's gonna catch cold, dontcha know! I hear Goss Harag materials make a toasty coat, think ya can get me some?

quests.name: White Knight on Ice
quests.description: My subordinates were quarreling with each other on a Barioth hunt, and their lack of unity caused the mission to end in failure—and fractures. We have other duties that we must attend to... Could perhaps you finish the job for us?

quests.name: My Ceanataur Gently Weeps
quests.description: I had planned a concert tour by boat, but as soon as we got the instruments loaded up and shipped off, a Shogun Ceanataur appeared to block our sea route. If you could hunt it, that'd be music to my ears!

quests.name: Trial of the Almudron
quests.description: I have to hunt an Almudron as a "test of courage," but look at me! This armor weighs more than I do. Ugh... Why do they want ME, of all people, to test my courage? There's none to test! Can you hunt this stupid monster for me?

quests.name: Pollution Problems
quests.description: Remobras and Ceanataurs are poppin' up everywhere in the Flooded Forest, pollutin' the waters with their poison. Soon the whole area'll turn into one big poison swamp! Do something before all the water turns purple!
quests.objective: Slay a total of 15 Ceanataur or Remobra
